revisions.description: - Added wlanAppVisibility to wlanTable.

- Added stationIPv6Address1, stationIPv6Address2, and stationIPv6Address3 to stationEventAlarm. - Added apTotalStationsAInOctets, apTotalStationsAOutOctets, apTotalStationsBInOctets, apTotalStationsBOutOctets, apTotalStationsGInOctets, apTotalStationsGOutOctets, apTotalStationsN50InOctets, apTotalStationsN50OutOctets, apTotalStationsN24InOctets, apTotalStationsN24OutOctets, apTotalStationsACInOctets, and apTotalStationsACOutOctets to apStatsTable.

- Modified the description of stationEventTimeStamp. - Added more access points (APs) to apPlatforms. - Deprecated topoWireStatTable. - Added topoCompleteStatTable. - Added applyMacAddressFormat to authenticationAdvanced. - Added radiusMacAddressFormatOption to vnsGlobalSetting.
- Modified the description of topoStatTable. - Modified the description of apPerformanceReportByRadioTable.

- Added wlanRadioManagement11k, wlanBeaconReport, QuietIE, wlanMirrorN, and wlanNetFlow to wlanTable. - Added wlanPrivfastTransition, and wlanPrivManagementFrameProtection to wlanPrivTable. - Added topologyIsGroup, topologyGroupMembers, and topologyMemberId to topologyTable. - Added netflowAndMirrorN Object. It contains netflowDestinationIP, netflowInterval, mirrorFirstN, and mirrorL2Ports. - Added fastTransition(13) to muDot11ConnectionCapability. - Added clearAccessRejectMsg and accessRejectMsgTable. - Added vnsQoSWirelessUseAdmControlBestEffort, and vnsQoSWirelessUseAdmControlBackground to vnsQoSTable. - Added maxBestEffortBWforReassociation, maxBestEffortBWforAssociation, maxBackgroundBWforReassociation, and maxBackgroundBWforAssociation to wirelessQoS. - Added radacctStartOnIPAddr and clientServiceTypeLogin to authenticationAdvanced. - Added apPerformanceReportByRadioTable. - Added apPerformanceReportbyRadioAndWlanTable. - Added apChannelUtilizationTable. - Added apAccessibilityTable. - Added apNeighboursTable.
- Added topoWireStatTable.

- Added firewallFriendlyExCP(7) to wlanAuthType. - Added firewallFriendlyExCP(7) to wlanCPAuthType. - Added wlanCPIdentity, wlanCPCustomSpecificURL and wlanCPSelectionOption to wlanCPTable. - Added wlanAuthRadiusOperatorNameSpace, wlanAuthRadiusOperatorName and wlanAuthMACBasedAuthReAuthOnAreaRoam to wlanAuthTable. - Added radiusExtnsSettingTable. - Added authenticationAdvanced. - Added areaChange(12) to stationEventType.

- Added apLogManagement Objects. - Added apMaintenanceCycle Objects. - Deprecated wlanCPExtTosValue from wlanCPTable. - Deprecated apSSHAccess from apTable. - Added apSSHConnection to apTable. - Added na(3) to apTelnetAccess.
- Added apRadioAttenuation to apRadioAntennaTable. - Added apRadioStatusTable. - Added apRadioProtocol to apRadioTable. - Deprecated apRadioType from apRadioTable.

- stationsByProtocol was modified to add stationsByProtocolUnavailable, stationsByProtocolError and stationsByProtocolAC. - Added muDot11ConnectionCapability to muTable. - deprecated muConnectionCapability from muTable. - Added ac(6) to muConnectionProtoco. - Added apInterfaceMTU, apEffectiveTunnelMTU and apTotalStationsAC to apStatsTable. - Added dot11ac(11) and dot11cStrict(12) to apRadioType. - Added wlanAuthRadiusAcctAfterMacBaseAuthorization and wlanAuthRadiusTimeoutRole to wlanAuthTable. - Added wlanPrivWPAversion to wlanPrivTable. - Added jumboFrames to physicalPortObjects. - Added apRegister to apEventId.
- apTable was modified to add apIPMulticastAssembly.

- Added wlanCPUseHTTPSforConnection to wlanCPTable. - Added wlanRadiusServerTable. - Added inSrvScanGrpDetectRogueAP and inSrvScanGrpListeningPort to inServiceScanGroupTable. - Added dedicatedScanGrpDetectRogueAP and dedicatedScanGrpListeningPort to dedicatedScanGroupTable. - Added clientAutologinOption to vnsGlobalSetting. - Added licenseMode, licenseLocalAP, licenseForeignAP, licenseLocalRadarAP and licenseForeignRadarAP to licensingInformation. - Added sysCPUType to systemObjects. - Added adHocModeDevice(6) and rogueAP(7) to dedicatedScanGrpCounterMeasures and inServiceScanGroupTable .
- Added AccessPoint reigisteration event notification.

- Added radiusFastFailoverEventsTable. - Addes dhcpRelayListenersTable. - topologyTable was modified to add new topologyDynamicEgress value.. - Added apRadioAntennaTable. - Added stationSessionNotifications trap. - scanGroupAPAssignmentTable was modified to add scanGroupAPAssignControllerIPAddress and scanGroupAPAssignFordwardingService. - scanAPTable was modified to add scanAPProfileName and scanAPProfileType. - Added dedicatedScanGroupTable. - apStatsTable was modified to add apInvalidPolicyCount. - apTable was modified to add apSecureDataTunnelType - uncategorizedAPTable was modified to add uncategorizedAPSSID and deprecate uncategorizedAPDescption.
Description changes for object groups: uncategorizedAPGroup, authorizedAPGroup and prohibitedAPGroup.
- Added radiusStrictMode - Enhance description field of a few variables

Added support: - widsWips: Configuration and statistic infromation about intrusion detection and prevention. - Controller dashboard information was added under 'dashboard', that includes some controler statistics and lincensing information - wlanSecurityReportTable was created to report on the status of weak WLAN configuration - apAntennaTable was added to provide AP antenna information - MU access list: creating MU access list using set of MAC addresses. - muACLTable is deprecated and replaced by muAccessListTable. - apTable was modified with added new field: apMICErrorWarning

Added support: - siteTable: main table to create any site. - sitePolicyTable: The table for assigning policies to a site. - siteCosTable: The table for retrieving assigned CoS to a site. - siteAPTable: Table for assinging APs to a site. - siteWlanTable: Table for assinging WLANs to a site. All tables above can collectively be used to configure a site or retrieve its configuration values. apTable was modified with new value for show its site membership. - WlanAuthTable::wlanAuthReplaceCalledStationIDWithZone was added. - WlanCpTable::wlanCPGuestMaxConcurrentSession was added. - TopologyTable was modified with additional new elements. - apTable was modified with new AP attributes. - muTable::muBSSIDMac was added. - loadGroupTable: more elements were added to this table. - loadGroupTable::loadGroupLoadControl was deprecated and was replaced with two new fields each representing one radio.
muTable was modified to show its association to WLAN by including WLAN ID into muTable.

secureConnection: This object was added to support weak cipher configuration. VSN related fields were modified: -- vnsFilterRuleDirection, vnsFilterRuleProtocol, vnsFilterRuleEtherType. muTable was modified with added fields: -- muTopologyName, muPolicyName, muDefaultCoS, muConnectionProtocol, muConnectionCapability. More added for configuration of MU Access List: - muACLType, muACLTable. apStatsTable was modified with more new elements: - apTotalStationsA, apTotalStationsB, apTotalStationsG,apTotalStationsN50, apTotalStationsN24.

Added layer two physical tables: - layerTwoPortTable Following tables are deprecated due to changes in EWC: - physicalPortsTable - phyDHCPRangeTable HWC (HiPath Wireless Controller) has been replaced with EWC (Enterasys Wireless Controller).

Added more tables to reflect WLAN configuration. Detailed WLAN configuration are reflected in new tables: - wlanPrivTable (WLAN privacy configuration) - wlanAuthTable (WLAN authentication configuration) - wlanRadiusTable (RADIUS assignment for each WLAN) - wlanCPTable (WLAN captive portal configuration) - wlanServiceType field was modifed to support mesh. Acess point related changes are: - apStaticMTUSize to apTable - apRadioNumber to apRadioTable - apRadioType to apRadioTable Global advanced filtering mode were added: advancedFilteringMode Following item were not applicable to HWC captive portal anymore and are deprecated: - cpLoginLabel - cpPasswordLabel - cpHeaderURL - cpFooterURL - cpMessage Access point load balancing group are reflected in new tables: - loadGroupTable (load group configuration) - loadGrpRadiosTable (radio assignment to loadGroupTable) - loadGrpWlanTable (WLAN assignment to loadGroupTable)

HWC release 7.31: Enhancement are in the area of: - availability: HWC availability support - vnManagerObjects: Mobility enhancement related to MU counters - tunnelStatsTable: Mobility tunnel stats enhancement such as MU counters - AP stats enhancement in apStatsTable - apRegistration: AP registration and administration configuration fields - topologyTable: Advanced topology configuration fields are added to this table. - topoStatTable: topoStatFrameChkSeqErrors and topoStatFrameTooLongErrors added - WLAN scalars added: wlanMaxEntries, wlanNumEntries, wlanTableNextAvailableIndex - wlanTable: Table of WLAN configuration - wlanStatsTable: WLAN statistics such as clients counts, RADIUS request counts, RAIDUS failed or rejected counters.

Obsoleted following items: - vnsAssignmentMode - vnsParentIfIndex - vnsRateControlProfTable - vnsWDSStatTable - vnsStatTable. These stats are reflected under topology - vnsExceptionStatTable. These stats are reflected under topology.
New changes include: - Topology configuratioin - Statistics about topoloy - Exception stat about topology.
Added version of the image for sensors.
Added SLP status field to VNS configuration table (vnsConfigTable).
Added information about sensor management.
Added new fields for VNS such as vnsEabled. Added AP filter for ACL list for Access Points
Added DNS entries. Aded DAS values Added RADIUS server information
DHCP information related to the Controller was added to the MIB.
Modified apTable with additional fields.
Added WDS VNS.
Initial version.

sysLogLevel.description: Sets the level of events which are written to the system log.

hiPathWirelessAppLogFacility.name: hiPathWirelessAppLogFacility
hiPathWirelessAppLogFacility.description: The application log facility level for syslog.

serviceLogFacility.name: serviceLogFacility
serviceLogFacility.description: The service log facility level for syslog.

includeAllServiceMessages.name: includeAllServiceMessages
includeAllServiceMessages.description: Indicates if DHCP messages should also be forwarded to syslog.

sysLogServersTable.name: sysLogServersTable
sysLogServersTable.description: Table of syslog servers to forward logging messages.

sysLogServersEntry.name: sysLogServersEntry
sysLogServersEntry.description: Configuration information for an external syslog server.

sysLogServerIndex.name: sysLogServerIndex
sysLogServerIndex.description: Table index for the syslog server.

sysLogServerEnabled.name: sysLogServerEnabled
sysLogServerEnabled.description: Indicates if messages are to be sent to the syslog server.

apLogCollectionEnable.name: apLogCollectionEnable
apLogCollectionEnable.description: If this field is set to true, then the AP log collection feature is enabled.

apLogFrequency.name: apLogFrequency
apLogFrequency.description: Number of log collections performed daily. The number must be one of the following 1, 2, 4, 6.

apLogDestination.name: apLogDestination
apLogDestination.description: Destination where the log file will be stored. If the local flash is not mounted, then you can not select 1. 0 : local memory. 1 : flash. 2 : remote location.

apLogFTProtocol.name: apLogFTProtocol
apLogFTProtocol.description: File transfer protocol. This field has meaning only when apLogDestination is set to remote(2). 0 : ftp. 1 : scp.

apLogServerIP.name: apLogServerIP
apLogServerIP.description: The IP address of the remote server. This field has meaning only when apLogDestination is set to remote(2).

apLogUserId.name: apLogUserId
apLogUserId.description: The user ID that is used for access to the remote server. This field has meaning only when apLogDestination is set to remote(2).

apLogPassword.name: apLogPassword
apLogPassword.description: The user password that is used for access to the remote server. This field has meaning only when apLogDestination is set to remote(2). This field can only be viewed in SNMPv3 mode with privacy.

apLogDirectory.name: apLogDirectory
apLogDirectory.description: The directory of the remote server. This field has meaning only when apLogDestination is set to remote(2).

apLogSelectedAPsTable.name: apLogSelectedAPsTable
apLogSelectedAPsTable.description: Table containing a list of APs for which log collection is supported.

apLogSelectedAPsEntry.name: apLogSelectedAPsEntry
apLogSelectedAPsEntry.description: Configuration information of an AP which supports the AP log feature.

apSerialNo.name: apSerialNo
apSerialNo.description: Table index for the apLogSelectedAPs. The AP's serial number serves as the index.

select.name: select
select.description: Indicates whether logs are collected from the AP.

apLogQuickSelectedOption.name: apLogQuickSelectedOption
apLogQuickSelectedOption.description: This is a quick select option for the user to perform the AP's bulk selection. This field is write-only and read access returns unknown(0) value. 0 : unknown. 1 : add all APs. 2 : add all local APs. 3 : add all foreign APs. 4 : remove all APs. 5 : remove all local APs. 6 : remove all foreign APs.

apLogFileUtilityLimit.name: apLogFileUtilityLimit
apLogFileUtilityLimit.description: The maximum number of AP log file copy requests that can be held in the apLogFileCopyTable. A value of 0 indicates no configured limit.

apLogFileUtilityCurrent.name: apLogFileUtilityCurrent
apLogFileUtilityCurrent.description: The number of AP log file copy requests currently in the apLogFileCopyTable.

apLogFileCopyTable.name: apLogFileCopyTable
apLogFileCopyTable.description: List of AP log file copy requests.

apLogFileCopyEntry.name: apLogFileCopyEntry
apLogFileCopyEntry.description: An entry describing the AP log file copy request.

apLogFileCopyIndex.name: apLogFileCopyIndex
apLogFileCopyIndex.description: The index for this AP log file copy request.

apLogFileCopyDestination.name: apLogFileCopyDestination
apLogFileCopyDestination.description: Destination where the log file will be copied. If the local flash is not mounted, then you can not select 1. 1 : copy the local AP log file to flash. 2 : copy the local AP log file to remote server.

apLogFileCopyProtocol.name: apLogFileCopyProtocol
apLogFileCopyProtocol.description: File transfer protocol to be used to copy the log file. 0 : ftp. 1 : scp.

apLogFileCopyServerIP.name: apLogFileCopyServerIP
apLogFileCopyServerIP.description: The IP address of the remote server.

apLogFileCopyUserID.name: apLogFileCopyUserID
apLogFileCopyUserID.description: The user ID that is used for access to the remote server.

apLogFileCopyPassword.name: apLogFileCopyPassword
apLogFileCopyPassword.description: The user password that is used for access to the remote server. This field can only be viewed in SNMPv3 mode with privacy.

apLogFileCopyServerDirectory.name: apLogFileCopyServerDirectory
apLogFileCopyServerDirectory.description: The directory on the remote server.

apLogFileCopyOperation.name: apLogFileCopyOperation
apLogFileCopyOperation.description: If this field is set to 1, then the controller will start to perform the copy action.

apLogFileCopyOperationStatus.name: apLogFileCopyOperationStatus
apLogFileCopyOperationStatus.description: The operational state of the AP log file copy request. inactive - Indicates that the RowStatus of this conceptual row is not in the `active` state. pending - Indicates that the AP log file copy described by this row is ready to run and waiting in a queue. running - Indicates that the AP log file copy described by this row is running. success - Indicates that the AP log file copy described by this row has successfully run to completion. failure - Indicates that the AP log file copy described by this row has failed to run to completion.

apLogFileCopyRowStatus.name: apLogFileCopyRowStatus
apLogFileCopyRowStatus.description: Row status variable for row operations on the apLogFileCopyTable.

primaryDNS.name: primaryDNS

secondaryDNS.name: secondaryDNS
secondaryDNS.description: Secondary DNS address configured in the Controller.

tertiaryDNS.name: tertiaryDNS

physicalPortsTable.name: physicalPortsTable
physicalPortsTable.description: Table of router ports on the controller.

portMgmtTrafficEnable.name: portMgmtTrafficEnable
portMgmtTrafficEnable.description: Determines whether controller management network traffic is allowed over this interface.

portDuplexMode.name: portDuplexMode
portDuplexMode.description: Duplex mode for the esa ports.

portFunction.name: portFunction
portFunction.description: Specifies the behavior of the EWC physical ports.

portEnabled.name: portEnabled
portEnabled.description: If enabled, the interface administratively is enabled.

portName.name: portName
portName.description: A textual string containing information about the port.

portIpAddress.name: portIpAddress
portIpAddress.description: The IP address of this port.

portMask.name: portMask
portMask.description: The subnet mask associated with the IP address of this port.

portVlanID.name: portVlanID
portVlanID.description: External VLAN tag for the physical port for trasmitted and received packets. Value ranges: (-1) it is not tagged, zero(0) means reserved, 1-4094 tag value.

portDHCPEnable.name: portDHCPEnable
portDHCPEnable.description: If enabled, the controller is configured as default DHCP server for AP.

portDHCPGateway.name: portDHCPGateway
portDHCPGateway.description: Gateway address to be supplied to the wireless clients if controller is configured as default DHCP server for AP.

portDHCPDomain.name: portDHCPDomain
portDHCPDomain.description: Domain name to be supplied to the wireless clients if controller is configured as default DHCP server for AP.

portDHCPDefaultLease.name: portDHCPDefaultLease
portDHCPDefaultLease.description: Default DHCP lease time in seconds to be supplied to the wireless clients if controller is configured as default DHCP server for AP.

portDHCPMaxLease.name: portDHCPMaxLease
portDHCPMaxLease.description: Maximum DHCP lease time in seconds to be supplied to the wireless clients if controller is configured as default DHCP server for AP.

portDHCPDnsServers.name: portDHCPDnsServers
portDHCPDnsServers.description: List of DNSs to be supplied to the wireless clients if controller is configured as default DHCP server for AP.

portDHCPWins.name: portDHCPWins
portDHCPWins.description: List of WINSs to be supplied to the wireless clients if controller is configured as default DHCP server for AP.

physicalPortsInternalVlanID.name: physicalPortsInternalVlanID
physicalPortsInternalVlanID.description: Internal VLAN tag to be used for physical ports for which the exernal VLAN tag have not been configured. Value ranges: (-1) it is not tagged, zero(0) means reserved, 1-4094 tag value.

phyDHCPRangeTable.name: phyDHCPRangeTable
phyDHCPRangeTable.description: phyDHCPRangeTable contains the IP address ranges that DHCP will serve to clients associated with physical ports.

phyDHCPRangeEntry.name: phyDHCPRangeEntry
phyDHCPRangeEntry.description: Configuration information for a DHCP range.

phyDHCPRangeIndex.name: phyDHCPRangeIndex
phyDHCPRangeIndex.description: Index for the DHCP row element.

phyDHCPRangeStart.name: phyDHCPRangeStart
phyDHCPRangeStart.description: First IP address in the range.

phyDHCPRangeEnd.name: phyDHCPRangeEnd
phyDHCPRangeEnd.description: Last IP address in the range.

phyDHCPRangeType.name: phyDHCPRangeType
phyDHCPRangeType.description: Determines whether addresses in the specified range will be included, or excluded by the DHCP server.

phyDHCPRangeStatus.name: phyDHCPRangeStatus
phyDHCPRangeStatus.description: Row status variable for row operations on the phyDHCPRangeTable

layerTwoPortTable.name: layerTwoPortTable
layerTwoPortTable.description: This table contains all layer two ports.

layerTwoPortEntry.name: layerTwoPortEntry
layerTwoPortEntry.description: Entry for a layer two port.

layerTwoPortName.name: layerTwoPortName
layerTwoPortName.description: Text string identifying the port within the controller.

layerTwoPortMgmtState.name: layerTwoPortMgmtState
layerTwoPortMgmtState.description: This value indicates administrator state of the port.

jumboFrames.name: jumboFrames
jumboFrames.description: Enables support for frames up to 1800 bytes long. jumboFrames support only applies to the controller and compatible APs.

vnRole.name: vnRole
vnRole.description: Specifies the role of this EWC in inter-EWC mobility. None indicates that mobile units cannot roam to or from this EWC. In any EWC cluster, only one EWC should be specified as vnMgr, all others should be have vnRole = vnAgent.

vnIfIndex.name: vnIfIndex
vnIfIndex.description: ifIndex of the physical port where inter-EWC tunnels terminate. This field has meaning if vnRole is not none(1)

vnHeartbeatInterval.name: vnHeartbeatInterval
vnHeartbeatInterval.description: The time interval between inter-EWC polling messages. This field has meaning if vnRole is not none(1)

vnLocalClients.name: vnLocalClients
vnLocalClients.description: Number of locally associated clients to this controller that is considered to be their home controller in the mobility zone, which this controller is part of.

vnForeignClients.name: vnForeignClients
vnForeignClients.description: Number of clients that have registered with another controller in the mobility zone, which this controller is part of, and currently have roamed to this controller.

vnTotalClients.name: vnTotalClients
vnTotalClients.description: Number of local and foreign clients on this controller in the Mobility zone.

ntpEnabled.name: ntpEnabled
ntpEnabled.description: Enable or disables support for the Network Time Protocol (NTP).

ntpTimezone.name: ntpTimezone
ntpTimezone.description: Specifies the time zone where this EWC resides.

ntpServerEnabled.name: ntpServerEnabled
ntpServerEnabled.description: Enable or disables support for controller as NTP server.

tunnelsTxRxBytes.name: tunnelsTxRxBytes
tunnelsTxRxBytes.description: Sum of transmitted and received bytes over all existing tunnels.

tunnelCount.name: tunnelCount
tunnelCount.description: Number of connections to other WirelessController controllers.

tunnelStatsTable.name: tunnelStatsTable
tunnelStatsTable.description: tunnelStatsTable contains a list of the IP tunnels connected to this EWC for use in inter-EWC mobility.

tunnelStartIP.name: tunnelStartIP
tunnelStartIP.description: IP address for the start of the tunnel.

tunnelStartHWC.name: tunnelStartHWC
tunnelStartHWC.description: Name of the access controller for the start of the tunnel.

tunnelEndIP.name: tunnelEndIP
tunnelEndIP.description: IP address for the end of the tunnel.

tunnelEndHWC.name: tunnelEndHWC
tunnelEndHWC.description: Name of the access controller for the end of the tunnel.

tunnelStatus.name: tunnelStatus
tunnelStatus.description: Indicates if the mobility tunnel is up or down.

tunnelStatsTxBytes.name: tunnelStatsTxBytes
tunnelStatsTxBytes.description: Number of bytes have been transmitted from the controller at the start of the tunnel to the controller on the other end of the tunnel.

tunnelStatsRxBytes.name: tunnelStatsRxBytes
tunnelStatsRxBytes.description: Number of bytes have been received by the controller at the end of the tunnel from the controller at the start of the tunnel.

tunnelStatsTxRxBytes.name: tunnelStatsTxRxBytes
tunnelStatsTxRxBytes.description: Sum of transmitted and received bytes over this tunnel.

clearAccessRejectMsg.name: clearAccessRejectMsg
clearAccessRejectMsg.description: Set this OID to one to erase the contents of the accessRejectMessage table. The OID always returns 0 when read.

accessRejectMsgTable.name: accessRejectMsgTable
accessRejectMsgTable.description: This table lists each of the reply messages returned in RADIUS Access-Reject messages and for each reply message, a count of the number of times it has been received.

accessRejectMsgEntry.name: accessRejectMsgEntry
accessRejectMsgEntry.description: One entry consisting of a unique Access-Reject Reply-Message (accessRejectReplyMessage) and count of this message.

armIndex.name: armIndex
armIndex.description: A number uniquely identifying each conceptual row in the accessRejectMsgTable.

armCount.name: armCount
armCount.description: Count of the number of times the controller has received an Access-Reject response from a RADIUS server that contained the associated armReplyMessage.

armReplyMessage.name: armReplyMessage
armReplyMessage.description: A reply message attribute received by the controller from a RADIUS server in an Access-Reject message.

availabilityStatus.name: availabilityStatus
availabilityStatus.description: This field can be used to enable or disable availability. If it is set to paired(1), then availability is enabled on this controller, otherwise it is considered that the controller operates in stand-alone mode. All other availability fields have no meaning if this field is set to standalone(0).

pairIPAddress.name: pairIPAddress
pairIPAddress.description: IP address of paired controller in availability pairing mode.

hwcAvailabilityRank.name: hwcAvailabilityRank
hwcAvailabilityRank.description: Rank of controller in Availability pairing mode. This is legacy field and applies to releases before 5.x and in current releases it is used for reporting only.

fastFailover.name: fastFailover
fastFailover.description: Enables or disables fast failover when controller operates in Availability pairing mode.

detectLinkFailure.name: detectLinkFailure
detectLinkFailure.description: Time to detect link failure between two controllers in availability pairing. The value can be set to values between 2-30 seconds

synchronizeSystemConfig.name: synchronizeSystemConfig
synchronizeSystemConfig.description: If this flag is set to enabled then system configuration is synchronized between paired controllers operating in Availabilty pairing mode.

synchronizeGuestPort.name: synchronizeGuestPort
synchronizeGuestPort.description: If this flag is set to enabled then Guest Portal user accounts are synchronized between paired controllers operating in Availabilty pairing mode.

weakCipherEnable.name: weakCipherEnable
weakCipherEnable.description: By default usage of weak cipher is enabled on EWC. Weak cipher can be disabled using this field.

licenseRegulatoryDomain.name: licenseRegulatoryDomain
licenseRegulatoryDomain.description: Regulatory domain that this wireless controller system has been licensed for to operate.

licenseType.name: licenseType
licenseType.description: Type of license for the controller. Temporary lincese allows controller to operate within defined number of days after which a permanent license is required for the operation of the controller system.

licenseDaysRemaining.name: licenseDaysRemaining
licenseDaysRemaining.description: Number of days is left for the temporary license to expire. This value has meaning if the license type is temporary(1).

licenseAvailableAP.name: licenseAvailableAP
licenseAvailableAP.description: If licenseMode is standAlone, this is the maximum number of APs that can be active on the controller without violating the licensing agreement. If licenseMode is availabilityPaired, this is the maximum number of APs that can be active on both members of the availability pair without violating the licensing agreement.

licenseInServiceRadarAP.name: licenseInServiceRadarAP
licenseInServiceRadarAP.description: If licenseMode is standalone this is the maximum number of APs that can be active on this controller and can operate as Guardians or in-service Radar APs without violating the licensing agreement. If licenseMode is availabilityPaired, this is the maximum number of APs that can be active on both members of the availability pair and can operate as Guardians or in-service Radar APs without violating the licensing agreement.

licenseMode.name: licenseMode
licenseMode.description: License mode determines how to interpret the license capacity OIDs. licenseMode is standalone if the controller is not part of an availability pair. licenseMode is availabilityPaired if the controller is part of an availability pair.

licenseLocalAP.name: licenseLocalAP
licenseLocalAP.description: The total number of AP capacity licenses installed on this controller.

licenseForeignAP.name: licenseForeignAP
licenseForeignAP.description: The total number of AP capacity licenses installed on this controller's availability partner.

licenseLocalRadarAP.name: licenseLocalRadarAP
licenseLocalRadarAP.description: The total number of AP Radar capacity licenses installed on this controller.

licenseForeignRadarAP.name: licenseForeignRadarAP
licenseForeignRadarAP.description: The total number of AP Radar capacity licenses installed on this controller's availability partner.

stationsByProtocolA.name: stationsByProtocolA
stationsByProtocolA.description: Number of stations using 802.11a mode to access the network.

stationsByProtocolB.name: stationsByProtocolB
stationsByProtocolB.description: Number of stations using 802.11b mode to access the network.

stationsByProtocolG.name: stationsByProtocolG
stationsByProtocolG.description: Number of stations using 802.11b mode to access the network.

stationsByProtocolN24.name: stationsByProtocolN24
stationsByProtocolN24.description: Number of stations using 802.11n mode with frequency of 2.4Gig to access the network.

stationsByProtocolN5.name: stationsByProtocolN5
stationsByProtocolN5.description: Number of stations using 802.11n mode with frequency of 5Gig to access the network.

stationsByProtocolUnavailable.name: stationsByProtocolUnavailable
stationsByProtocolUnavailable.description: The total number of stations with sessions on this controller for which the 802.11 protocol type (a, b, g, n, ac) for which the protocol could not be determined.

stationsByProtocolError.name: stationsByProtocolError
stationsByProtocolError.description: The total number of stations with sessions on this controller for which an AP reported an invalid (out of range) value as the station's 802.11 protocol type.

stationsByProtocolAC.name: stationsByProtocolAC
stationsByProtocolAC.description: Number of stations using 802.11ac mode to access the network.

apByChannelTable.name: apByChannelTable
apByChannelTable.description: List of aggregated access points that are operating on a specific wireless channels.

apByChannelEntry.name: apByChannelEntry
apByChannelEntry.description: An entry in this table for one wireless channel and aggregated access point on that channel.

apByChannelNumber.name: apByChannelNumber
apByChannelNumber.description: The channel on which a set of access points are presently operating. If this number is 0, this means the AP is in Guardian mode or the AP's radios are turned off.

apByChannelAPs.name: apByChannelAPs
apByChannelAPs.description: Total number of the access point on the channel that this row is indexed on.

vnsCount.name: vnsCount
vnsCount.description: Number of VNSes defined in vnsConfigTable.

vnsConfigTable.name: vnsConfigTable
vnsConfigTable.description: Contains definitions of the Virtual Network Segments defined on this WirelessController.

vnsConfigEntry.name: vnsConfigEntry
vnsConfigEntry.description: Configuration elements for a specific Virtual Network Segment.

vnsAssignmentMode.name: vnsAssignmentMode
vnsAssignmentMode.description: Determines the method by which mobile units are assigned an address within this VNS. If vnsAssignmentMode = ssid, any client with an SSID matching the VNS will be assigned an address from this VNS. If vnsAssignmentMode == aaa, then address assignment is not completed until after the user is authenticated.

vnsMUSessionTimeout.name: vnsMUSessionTimeout
vnsMUSessionTimeout.description: Client session idle time out, in seconds.

vnsAllowMulticast.name: vnsAllowMulticast
vnsAllowMulticast.description: When true, allows IP multicast packets to be broadcast to the clients on this VNS.

vnsSSID.name: vnsSSID
vnsSSID.description: Service Set Identifier (i.e. Network Name) that will be configured on the AccessPoints associated with this VNS.

vnsDomain.name: vnsDomain
vnsDomain.description: Domain name to be supplied to the wireless clients if internal DHCP address assignment.

vnsDNSServers.name: vnsDNSServers
vnsDNSServers.description: List of DNSs to be supplied to the wireless clients if internal DHCP address assignment.

vnsWINSServers.name: vnsWINSServers
vnsWINSServers.description: List of WINSs to be supplied to the wireless clients if internal DHCP address assignment.

vnsAuthModel.name: vnsAuthModel
vnsAuthModel.description: vnsAuthModel specifies the authentication method used for clients in the VNS. None indicates that the VNS is open, and no authentication is required. vnsAuthModel=captivePortal may only be specified for a VNS with vnsAssignmentMode=ssid. Likewise, vnsAuthModel=dot1X may only be specified for a VNS with vnsAssignmentMode=aaa.

vnsParentIfIndex.name: vnsParentIfIndex
vnsParentIfIndex.description: Specifies the ifIndex of the parent VNS, if this VNS is a child. If this is a top level VNS, vnsParentIfIndex will return null or 0.

vnsMgmtTrafficEnable.name: vnsMgmtTrafficEnable
vnsMgmtTrafficEnable.description: Specifies whether clients in the VNS have access to EWC management elements.

vnsUseDHCPRelay.name: vnsUseDHCPRelay
vnsUseDHCPRelay.description: This variable indicates what type of DHCP is used for the VNS. none(0): No DHCP server on the VNS. dhcpRelay(1): Uses DHCP relay to reach the DHCP server. localDhcp(2): Uses local DHCP server on the controler.

vns3rdPartyAP.name: vns3rdPartyAP
vns3rdPartyAP.description: When true, specifies that the VNS contains 3rd party access points. Only one such VNS may be defined for a WirelessController.

vnsStatus.name: vnsStatus
vnsStatus.description: RowStatus variable for performing row operations on vnsConfigTable.

vnsMode.name: vnsMode
vnsMode.description: Type of traffic for this VNS. routed(1): The traffic is routed at the controller. bridgeAtController(2): Traffic is bridged at controller. bridgeAtAP(3): Traffic is bridged at Access Points. wds(4): Wireless Distributed System (WDS) type of VNS. If VNS is type of wds(4), then only vnsSupressSSID, vnsDescription and vnsSSID has meaning.

vnsVlanID.name: vnsVlanID
vnsVlanID.description: VLAN tag for the packets trasmitted to/from of the VNS. This value has meaning if vnsMode is bridgeAtController(2) or bridgeAtAP(3). If vnsMode = bridgeAtController(2), tagging is done at controller. If vnsMode = bridgeAtAP(3), tagging is done at Access Point. Value ranges: (-1) it is not tagged, zero(0) means reserved, 1-4094 tag value.

vnsInterfaceName.name: vnsInterfaceName
vnsInterfaceName.description: Physical interface to be used in the controller for trasmitting/receiving packets for the VNS. This value has meaning if vnsMode is bridgeAtController(2).

vnsMgmIpAddress.name: vnsMgmIpAddress
vnsMgmIpAddress.description: IP address of the management port associated to this VNS. This value has meaning if vnsMode is bridgeAtController(2).

vnsSuppressSSID.name: vnsSuppressSSID
vnsSuppressSSID.description: If set to true, this prevents this SSID from appearing in the beacon message.

vnsApplyPowerBackOff.name: vnsApplyPowerBackOff
vnsApplyPowerBackOff.description: Indicates whether the AP will direct 802.11h-enabled clients to apply the same power back-off setting that the AP is using

vnsProcessClientIEReq.name: vnsProcessClientIEReq
vnsProcessClientIEReq.description: If true, enables support for 802.11d client information request.

vnsDLSSupportEnable.name: vnsDLSSupportEnable
vnsDLSSupportEnable.description: If true, enables support for DLS Support. This value has meaning only if vnsUseDHCPRelay is selected as localDhcp(2) and vnsMode is select as either routed(1) or bridgeAtController(2).

vnsDLSAddress.name: vnsDLSAddress
vnsDLSAddress.description: DNS IP Address for DLS associated to this VNS. It could be IP address or Name

vnsDLSPort.name: vnsDLSPort
vnsDLSPort.description: DNS Port for DLS associated to this VNS.

vnsRateControlProfile.name: vnsRateControlProfile
vnsRateControlProfile.description: The Rate Control Profile that is referenced by this VNS.

vnsSessionAvailabilityEnable.name: vnsSessionAvailabilityEnable
vnsSessionAvailabilityEnable.description: To indicate if Session Availability feature is enabled.

vnsEnabled.name: vnsEnabled
vnsEnabled.description: VNS status of being enabled or disabled.

vnsStrictSubnetAdherence.name: vnsStrictSubnetAdherence
vnsStrictSubnetAdherence.description: Subnet adherence verification status for the VNS. Controller only learns devices whose address is within range of VNS segment definition. Disabling this field causes to not enforce validation. Doing so, may expose the controller to in-advertent Learning DoS attacks.

vnsSLPEnabled.name: vnsSLPEnabled
vnsSLPEnabled.description: Status of SLP flag on Bridge at Controller type VNS. This field does not have any meaning for other types of VNS.

vnsConfigWLANID.name: vnsConfigWLANID
vnsConfigWLANID.description: Creation of VNS requires existing of a free WLAN. One WLAN can only be used in one VNS only. This ID identifies the WLAN that is used for creation of VNS that is identified by this row.

vnsDHCPRangeTable.name: vnsDHCPRangeTable
vnsDHCPRangeTable.description: vnsDHCPRangeTable contains the IP address ranges that DHCP will serve to clients associated with this VNS.

vnsDHCPRangeEntry.name: vnsDHCPRangeEntry
vnsDHCPRangeEntry.description: Configuration information for a DHCP range.

vnsDHCPRangeIndex.name: vnsDHCPRangeIndex
vnsDHCPRangeIndex.description: Index for the DHCP row element.

vnsDHCPRangeStart.name: vnsDHCPRangeStart
vnsDHCPRangeStart.description: First IP address in the range.

vnsDHCPRangeEnd.name: vnsDHCPRangeEnd
vnsDHCPRangeEnd.description: Last IP address in the range.

vnsDHCPRangeType.name: vnsDHCPRangeType
vnsDHCPRangeType.description: Determines whether addresses in the specified range will be included, or excluded by the DHCP server.

vnsDHCPRangeStatus.name: vnsDHCPRangeStatus
vnsDHCPRangeStatus.description: Row status variable for row operations on the vnsDHCPRangeTable

vnsCaptivePortalTable.name: vnsCaptivePortalTable
vnsCaptivePortalTable.description: Details of the Captive Portal login page for VNSes that have vnsAssignment=ssid and vnsAuthModel=captivePortal.

vnsCaptivePortalEntry.name: vnsCaptivePortalEntry
vnsCaptivePortalEntry.description: Captive Portal Information for the VNS.

cpURL.name: cpURL
cpURL.description: Redirect URL of the Captive Portal login page.

cpLoginLabel.name: cpLoginLabel
cpLoginLabel.description: Label that appears in front of the login field on the Captive Portal login page.

cpPasswordLabel.name: cpPasswordLabel
cpPasswordLabel.description: Label that appears in front of the password field on the Captive Portal login page.

cpHeaderURL.name: cpHeaderURL
cpHeaderURL.description: URL of the Captive Portal header.

cpFooterURL.name: cpFooterURL
cpFooterURL.description: URL of the Captive Portal footer.

cpMessage.name: cpMessage
cpMessage.description: A welcome message, or set of instructions that is to appear on the Captive Portal login page.

cpReplaceGatewayWithFQDN.name: cpReplaceGatewayWithFQDN
cpReplaceGatewayWithFQDN.description: Fully Qualified Domain Name (FQDN) to be used as the gateway IP address.

cpDefaultRedirectionURL.name: cpDefaultRedirectionURL
cpDefaultRedirectionURL.description: Default Redirect URL of the Captive Portal login page.

cpConnectionIP.name: cpConnectionIP
cpConnectionIP.description: IP address of the Controller interface for Captive Portal.

cpConnectionPort.name: cpConnectionPort
cpConnectionPort.description: Port number on the cpConnectionIP interface.

cpSharedSecret.name: cpSharedSecret
cpSharedSecret.description: Secret Key to be used to encrypt the information passed between the Controller and the external web server. It is the password common to both Controller and the external web server.

cpLogOff.name: cpLogOff
cpLogOff.description: Toggles the display of logoff popup screen, allowing users to control their logoff.

cpStatusCheck.name: cpStatusCheck
cpStatusCheck.description: Toggles the display of popup window with session statistics for users to monitor their usage and time left in session.

cpType.name: cpType
cpType.description: Type of captive portal is enabled for the selected VNS. none(1) = no captive portal configured or type is unknown. internal(2) = internal captive portal. external(4) = external captive portal. guestPortal (5) = open host captive portal.

vnsRadiusServerTable.name: vnsRadiusServerTable
vnsRadiusServerTable.description: List of RADIUS servers to be utilized for authentication in the VNS.

vnsRadiusServerEntry.name: vnsRadiusServerEntry
vnsRadiusServerEntry.description: Configuration information for a RADIUS server.

vnsRadiusServerPort.name: vnsRadiusServerPort
vnsRadiusServerPort.description: Port number for the RADIUS server.

vnsRadiusServerRetries.name: vnsRadiusServerRetries
vnsRadiusServerRetries.description: Number of retries for a RADIUS authentication request.

vnsRadiusServerSharedSecret.name: vnsRadiusServerSharedSecret
vnsRadiusServerSharedSecret.description: Shared secret to be used between the NAS and RADIUS server.

vnsRadiusServerNASIdentifier.name: vnsRadiusServerNASIdentifier
vnsRadiusServerNASIdentifier.description: NAS identifier to be included in RADIUS request.

vnsRadiusServerNasAddress.name: vnsRadiusServerNasAddress
vnsRadiusServerNasAddress.description: NAS address to be included in RADIUS request.

vnsFilterIDTable.name: vnsFilterIDTable
vnsFilterIDTable.description: Table of names filters for a VNS.

vnsFilterIDEntry.name: vnsFilterIDEntry
vnsFilterIDEntry.description: Name of a specific filter in the VNS.

vnsFilterRuleTable.name: vnsFilterRuleTable
vnsFilterRuleTable.description: Table containing specific filters for a named filter.

vnsFilterRuleEntry.name: vnsFilterRuleEntry
vnsFilterRuleEntry.description: Filter elements for an individual VNS filter.

vnsFilterRuleOrder.name: vnsFilterRuleOrder
vnsFilterRuleOrder.description: Position of the filter in the filter list.

vnsFilterRuleDirection.name: vnsFilterRuleDirection
vnsFilterRuleDirection.description: Traffic direction defined by the rule.

vnsFilterRuleAction.name: vnsFilterRuleAction
vnsFilterRuleAction.description: Allow or deny traffic for the filter.

vnsFilterRuleIPAddress.name: vnsFilterRuleIPAddress
vnsFilterRuleIPAddress.description: IP address to apply the filter.

vnsFilterRulePortLow.name: vnsFilterRulePortLow
vnsFilterRulePortLow.description: Low port number for the filter.

vnsFilterRulePortHigh.name: vnsFilterRulePortHigh
vnsFilterRulePortHigh.description: High port number for the filter.

vnsPrivacyTable.name: vnsPrivacyTable
vnsPrivacyTable.description: Table of privacy settings for the VNS.

vnsPrivacyEntry.name: vnsPrivacyEntry
vnsPrivacyEntry.description: Configuration values for a specific privacy setting.

vnsPrivWEPKeyType.name: vnsPrivWEPKeyType
vnsPrivWEPKeyType.description: Type of key in use. none(1) = not cofigured, wepstatic(2) = static WEP, wpapsk(3) = WPA Pre-Shared Key, dynamic(4) = dynamically assigned, wpa(5) = WPA.

vnsPrivDynamicRekeyFrequency.name: vnsPrivDynamicRekeyFrequency
vnsPrivDynamicRekeyFrequency.description: Dynamic WEP re-keying frequency, in seconds. Setting this value to 0 disables rekeying. This value is only meaningful if vnsPrivWEPKeyType = wpapsk(3). For any other values of vnsPrivWEPKeyType, reading or setting this value will return an unsuccessful status and will return a value of null or zero.

vnsPrivWEPKeyLength.name: vnsPrivWEPKeyLength
vnsPrivWEPKeyLength.description: WEP key length, 64, 128, or 152 bits. If vnsPrivWEPKeyType is none, reading or setting this value will return an unsuccessful status and will return a value of null or zero.

vnsPrivUseSharedKey.name: vnsPrivUseSharedKey
vnsPrivUseSharedKey.description: Enables the use of WPA shared key for this VNS.

vnsPrivWPASharedKey.name: vnsPrivWPASharedKey
vnsPrivWPASharedKey.description: The value of the WPA shared key for this VNS. This value is logically WRITE ONLY. Attempts to read this value shall return unsuccessful status and values of null or zero.

vnsPrivWPA2Enabled.name: vnsPrivWPA2Enabled
vnsPrivWPA2Enabled.description: When true, WPA v.2 support is enabled.

vnsWEPKeyTable.name: vnsWEPKeyTable
vnsWEPKeyTable.description: Table of WEP key entries for a static WEP definition.

vnsWEPKeyEntry.name: vnsWEPKeyEntry
vnsWEPKeyEntry.description: WEP key for a single entry in the table.

vnsWEPKeyIndex.name: vnsWEPKeyIndex
vnsWEPKeyIndex.description: Table index for the WEP key.

vnsWEPKeyValue.name: vnsWEPKeyValue
vnsWEPKeyValue.description: Value of a WEP key for this VNS. This value is logically WRITE ONLY. Attempts to read this value shall return unsuccessful status and values of null or zero.

vns3rdPartyAPTable.name: vns3rdPartyAPTable
vns3rdPartyAPTable.description: Contains a list of 3rd Party access points for the EWC.

vns3rdPartyAPEntry.name: vns3rdPartyAPEntry
vns3rdPartyAPEntry.description: Configuration information for a 3rd party access point.

apMacAddress.name: apMacAddress
apMacAddress.description: Ethernet MAC address of the 3rd party access point.

apIpAddress.name: apIpAddress
apIpAddress.description: IP address of the 3rd party access point.

vnsQoSTable.name: vnsQoSTable
vnsQoSTable.description: This table contains list of per-VNS QoS related configuration.

vnsQoSEntry.name: vnsQoSEntry
vnsQoSEntry.description: An entry related to QoS configuration for the VNS indexed by vnsIfIndex.

vnsQoSWirelessLegacyFlag.name: vnsQoSWirelessLegacyFlag
vnsQoSWirelessLegacyFlag.description: This variable is used to enable/disable legacy QoS feature.

vnsQoSWirelessWMMFlag.name: vnsQoSWirelessWMMFlag
vnsQoSWirelessWMMFlag.description: This variable is used to enable/disable WMM feature.

vnsQoSWireless80211eFlag.name: vnsQoSWireless80211eFlag
vnsQoSWireless80211eFlag.description: This variable is used to enable/disable 802.11e feature.

vnsQoSWirelessTurboVoiceFlag.name: vnsQoSWirelessTurboVoiceFlag
vnsQoSWirelessTurboVoiceFlag.description: This variable is used to enable/disable turbo feature.

vnsQoSPriorityOverrideFlag.name: vnsQoSPriorityOverrideFlag
vnsQoSPriorityOverrideFlag.description: Enable/disable the use of DSCP to override Servic Class (SC) value.

vnsQoSPriorityOverrideSC.name: vnsQoSPriorityOverrideSC
vnsQoSPriorityOverrideSC.description: Service class (SC) of the override value. This field has a meaning if vnsQoSPriorityOverrideFlag is enabled.

vnsQoSPriorityOverrideDSCP.name: vnsQoSPriorityOverrideDSCP
vnsQoSPriorityOverrideDSCP.description: DSCP override value to be used for the service class. This field has a meaning if vnsQoSPriorityOverrideFlag is enabled.

vnsQoSClassificationServiceClass.name: vnsQoSClassificationServiceClass
vnsQoSClassificationServiceClass.description: Service Class value for the DSCP code. This field is 64-bytes long. Each byte represents mapping between DSCP and Service Class. Position of each byte in the array represents DSCP code and the content of each byte represents the service class value for that DSCP code. For example, second byte represents DSCP code 1 and its value represents SC value. Value for each byte is equivalent to either of: background = 0, bestEffort = 1, bronze = 2, silver = 3, gold = 4, platinum = 5, premiumVoice = 6, networkControl = 7

vnsQoSWirelessEnableUAPSD.name: vnsQoSWirelessEnableUAPSD
vnsQoSWirelessEnableUAPSD.description: This variable is used to enable/disable U-APSD feature.

vnsQoSWirelessUseAdmControlVoice.name: vnsQoSWirelessUseAdmControlVoice
vnsQoSWirelessUseAdmControlVoice.description: If enabled, admission control for voice traffic is used.

vnsQoSWirelessUseAdmControlVideo.name: vnsQoSWirelessUseAdmControlVideo
vnsQoSWirelessUseAdmControlVideo.description: If enabled, admission control for vedio traffic is used. This field has a meaning if vnsQoSUseGlobalAdmVoice is enabled.

vnsQoSWirelessULPolicerAction.name: vnsQoSWirelessULPolicerAction
vnsQoSWirelessULPolicerAction.description: If doNothing is selected, no action is taken. This is default value. If sendDELTStoClient is selected, AP will send DELTS if a client is abusing in uplink. This field has a meaning only if admission control is enabled for VO or VI.

vnsQoSWirelessDLPolicerAction.name: vnsQoSWirelessDLPolicerAction
vnsQoSWirelessDLPolicerAction.description: If doNothing is selected, no action is taken. This is default value. If downgrade is selected, AP will downgrade all traffic to the highest AC that does not require CAC in downlink. If drop is selected, AP will drop client if it observes a client that is illegally using an AC that has CAC mandatory in downlink. This field has a meaning only if admission control is enabled for VO or VI.

vnsQoSWirelessUseAdmControlBestEffort.name: vnsQoSWirelessUseAdmControlBestEffort
vnsQoSWirelessUseAdmControlBestEffort.description: If enabled, admission control for video traffic is set to Best Effort. This field has a meaning if vnsQoSUseGlobalAdmVoice is enabled.

vnsQoSWirelessUseAdmControlBackground.name: vnsQoSWirelessUseAdmControlBackground
vnsQoSWirelessUseAdmControlBackground.description: If enabled, admission control for video traffic is set to Background. This field has a meaning if vnsQoSUseGlobalAdmVoice is enabled.

vnsWDSRFTable.name: vnsWDSRFTable
vnsWDSRFTable.description: ontains definitions of the Wireless Distirbution System (WDS) VNS defined on this Controller.

vnsWDSRFEntry.description: Configuration elements for a specific WDS VNS.

vnsWDSRFbgService.name: vnsWDSRFbgService
vnsWDSRFbgService.description: Type of service offered by this radio.

vnsWDSRFaService.name: vnsWDSRFaService
vnsWDSRFaService.description: Type of service offered by this radio.

vnsRateControlProfEntry.description: Name of a specific Rate Control Profile.

vnsRateControlProfInd.name: vnsRateControlProfInd
vnsRateControlProfInd.description: A monotonically increasing integer which acts as index of entries within the named Rate Control Profiles.

vnsRateControlCIR.name: vnsRateControlCIR
vnsRateControlCIR.description: Rate Control Average Rate (CIR) in kbps.

vnsRateControlCBS.name: vnsRateControlCBS
vnsRateControlCBS.description: Rate Control Burst Size (CBS) in bytes.

vnsAPFilterTable.description: Filters applied to Access Points via VNS settings and assignments.

vnsAPFilterEntry.description: An entry containing filters definition for Access Points assigned to VNS that is identified by VNS index.

vnsAPFilterRuleOrder.description: Position of the filter in the filter list.

vnsAPFilterRuleDirection.name: vnsAPFilterRuleDirection
vnsAPFilterRuleDirection.description: Traffic direction related to the filter rule.

vnsAPFilterAction.name: vnsAPFilterAction
vnsAPFilterAction.description: Allow or deny traffic for the filter.

vnsAPFilterIPAddress.name: vnsAPFilterIPAddress
vnsAPFilterIPAddress.description: IP address applied to the filter.

vnsAPFilterMask.name: vnsAPFilterMask
vnsAPFilterMask.description: The mask, number of bits set to one in the mask, applied to filter IP address.

vnsAPFilterPortLow.name: vnsAPFilterPortLow
vnsAPFilterPortLow.description: Low port number for the filter.

vnsAPFilterPortHigh.name: vnsAPFilterPortHigh
vnsAPFilterPortHigh.description: High port number for the filter.

vnsAPFilterRowStatus.name: vnsAPFilterRowStatus
vnsAPFilterRowStatus.description: RowStatus value for this table entry.

vnsStatRadiusTotRequests.name: vnsStatRadiusTotRequests
vnsStatRadiusTotRequests.description: Total requests sent to radius server.

vnsStatRadiusReqFailed.name: vnsStatRadiusReqFailed
vnsStatRadiusReqFailed.description: Requests that failed to be processed by radius server.

vnsStatRadiusReqRejected.name: vnsStatRadiusReqRejected
vnsStatRadiusReqRejected.description: Requests that have been rejected by radius server.

vnsExceptionStatPktsDenied.name: vnsExceptionStatPktsDenied
vnsExceptionStatPktsDenied.description: Total packets that are denied by defined filters.

vnsExceptionStatPktsAllowed.name: vnsExceptionStatPktsAllowed
vnsExceptionStatPktsAllowed.description: Total packets that are allowed by defined filters.

vnsWDSStatAPRole.name: vnsWDSStatAPRole
vnsWDSStatAPRole.description: Role of the AP in WDS tree. All the statistics and configuration information in this table has no meaning if the role is unknown(-1).

vnsWDSStatAPRadio.name: vnsWDSStatAPRadio
vnsWDSStatAPRadio.description: Radio and freq on which uplink WDS is established, N/A if connected over etherent (value are 'a:<freq>', 'b/g:<freq>', or 'N/A')

vnsWDSStatAPParent.name: vnsWDSStatAPParent
vnsWDSStatAPParent.description: AP Name of the parent AP.

vnsWDSStatSSID.name: vnsWDSStatSSID
vnsWDSStatSSID.description: SSID of the WDS VNS where parent WDS link is established.

vnsWDSStatRxFrame.name: vnsWDSStatRxFrame
vnsWDSStatRxFrame.description: Received frames from the parent AP.

vnsWDSStatTxFrame.name: vnsWDSStatTxFrame
vnsWDSStatTxFrame.description: Transmitted frames to the parent AP.

vnsWDSStatRxError.name: vnsWDSStatRxError
vnsWDSStatRxError.description: Received frames in error from the parent AP.

vnsWDSStatTxError.name: vnsWDSStatTxError
vnsWDSStatTxError.description: Transmitted frames in error to the parent AP.

maxVoiceBWforReassociation.description: Maximum voice bandwidth to be used for re-association.

maxVoiceBWforAssociation.description: Maximum voice bandwidth to be used for association.

maxVideoBWforReassociation.description: Maximum video bandwidth to be used for re-association.

maxBestEffortBWforReassociation.description: Maximum best effort bandwidth to be used for reassociation.

maxBestEffortBWforAssociation.description: Maximum best effort bandwidth to be used for association.

maxBackgroundBWforReassociation.description: Maximum background bandwidth to be used for reassociation.
