maxBackgroundBWforAssociation.description: Maximum background bandwidth to be used for association.

externalRadiusServerTable.name: externalRadiusServerTable
externalRadiusServerTable.description: Table of external RADIUS servers available for authentication services.

externalRadiusServerEntry.name: externalRadiusServerEntry
externalRadiusServerEntry.description: Configuration information about the RADIUS server entry.

externalRadiusServerAddress.name: externalRadiusServerAddress
externalRadiusServerAddress.description: RADIUS server address, it can be either string or IP address.

externalRadiusServerSharedSecret.name: externalRadiusServerSharedSecret
externalRadiusServerSharedSecret.description: Shared secret between Radius and the client.

dasReplayInterval.name: dasReplayInterval
dasReplayInterval.description: The time window for message timeliness and replay protection for DAS packets. Packets should be dropped that their time generation is outside of this specified interval. Value zero indicates that the timeliness checking will be performed.

advancedFilteringMode.name: advancedFilteringMode
advancedFilteringMode.description: Value of 'enabled(1)' means EWC is operating in advanced filtering configuration mode. Value of 'disabled(0)' means EWC is operating in mode that is compatible with releases prior to 7.41. This field can only be set to 'enabled(1)' and after setting it to that value, the only way to undo that is by resetting the database.

radiusStrictMode.name: radiusStrictMode
radiusStrictMode.description: If this variable set to true, then assignment of RADIUS server(s) to WLAN are automatic during WLAN creation, otherwise, assignment of RADIUS server(s) to WLAN must be done manually.

radiusFastFailoverEventsTable.name: radiusFastFailoverEventsTable
radiusFastFailoverEventsTable.description: Table in which to configure which RADIUS servers will be sent interim accounting reports for stations when a fast failover incident occurs

radiusFastFailoverEventsEntry.name: radiusFastFailoverEventsEntry
radiusFastFailoverEventsEntry.description: An entry for each radius server.

radiusFFOEid.name: radiusFFOEid
radiusFFOEid.description: The IP address or hostname of configured radius server. If the hostname is created from GUI/CLI and the size is bigger than 64 characters, snmp will display the first 64 characters only.

fastFailoverEvents.name: fastFailoverEvents
fastFailoverEvents.description: If true, send an interim accounting record to the RADIUS server for each affected station when a fast failover event occurs. This field can be modified when controller is operated in availablity paired mode and fast failover is enabled

dhcpRelayListenersMaxEntries.name: dhcpRelayListenersMaxEntries
dhcpRelayListenersMaxEntries.description: Maximum number of servers to which DHCP messages are relayed .

dhcpRelayListenersNumEntries.name: dhcpRelayListenersNumEntries
dhcpRelayListenersNumEntries.description: The current number of entries in the dhcpRelayListenersTable.

dhcpRelayListenersNextIndex.name: dhcpRelayListenersNextIndex
dhcpRelayListenersNextIndex.description: This object indicates numerically lowest available index within this entity, which may be used for the value of index in the creation of new entry in dhcpRelayListenersTable. An index is considered available if the index falls within the range of 1 to dhcpRelayListenersMaxEntries and it is not being used to index an existing entry in the dhcpRelayListenersTable contained this entity. This value should only be used as guideline for the management application and there is no requirement on the management application to create entries based upon this index value. Value of zero indicates there is no more room for new dhcpRelayListenersTable creation.

dhcpRelayListenersTable.name: dhcpRelayListenersTable
dhcpRelayListenersTable.description: A list of servers to which DHCP messages are relayed but from which no responses are expected.

dhcpRelayListenersID.name: dhcpRelayListenersID
dhcpRelayListenersID.description: The id corresponds to the 'server number' in the controller GUI and CLI.

dhcpRelayListenersRowStatus.name: dhcpRelayListenersRowStatus
dhcpRelayListenersRowStatus.description: This object allows dynamic creation and deletion of entries within dhcpRelayListenersTable as well as activation and deactivation of these entries. For row creation, EWC only supports creatAndWait.

destinationName.name: destinationName
destinationName.description: Text string uniquely identifying NAC Server Name. Allowable characters for this field are from the set of A-Z, a-z, -_!#$, 0-9, and space. max len is 63 chars Howerver, it is recommended to avoid leading and trailing spaces.

destinationIP.name: destinationIP
destinationIP.description: IPv4 address to which DHCP messages are relayed.

clientAutologinOption.name: clientAutologinOption
clientAutologinOption.description: Many devices such as those made by Apple(R) implement an autologin feature that prompts the user to login as soon as the device detects the presence of a Captive Portal. This feature sometimes causes problems for users who actually interact with the captive portal. hide(0) - Hide the captive portal from Autologin detector. redirect(1) - Redirect detection messages to the Captive Portal. This option is to allow client autologin to detect the captive portal & prompt the user to login. This may cause post-authentication redirection to fail. drop(2) - Drop detection messages.

includeServiceType.name: includeServiceType
includeServiceType.description: Include the Service-Type attribute in client access request messages when this field is set to enable(1).

clientMessageDelayTime.name: clientMessageDelayTime
clientMessageDelayTime.description: This field specifies how long, in seconds, the notice Web page is displayed to the client when the topology changes as a result of a role change. The notice Web page indicates that authentication was successful and that the user must close all browser windows and then restart the browser for access to the network. Currently this is supported for Internal Captive Portal, Guest Portal, and Guest Splash.

radiusAccounting.name: radiusAccounting
radiusAccounting.description: This field enables or disables RADIUS accounting. Disabling RADIUS accounting overrides the RADIUS accounting settings of individual WLAN Services. Enabling RADIUS accounting activates RADIUS accounting only in WLAN Services specifically configured to perform it.

serverUsageModel.name: serverUsageModel
serverUsageModel.description: This field specifies RADIUS server failover behavior when the primary server goes down. When the primary server is down the controller moves on to the secondary or tertiary configured RADIUS Servers. If this field is set to primaryBackup(1), then the controller starts polling the primary RADIUS server to see if it is up. When the primary RADIUS server comes back, the controller automatically starts sending new access requests to the primary RADIUS server but pending requests continue with backup RADIUS server. The administrator can select between the two strategies, i.e. the existing roundRobin(0) or new primaryBackup(1). This only applies to Authentication, not to Accounting.

radacctStartOnIPAddr.name: radacctStartOnIPAddr
radacctStartOnIPAddr.description: When this OID is set to disabled (0) the controller sends a RADIUS accounting start message as soon as it receives an Access-Accept for the user from a RADIUS server. When this OID is set to enabled(1) the controller defers sending the RADIUS accounting start message until an Access-Accept for the client is received and the client's IP address is known.

clientServiceTypeLogin.name: clientServiceTypeLogin
clientServiceTypeLogin.description: When this OID is set to enabled(1) the controller sets the Service-Type attribute of a station's Access-Request to 'Login'. When this OID is set to disabled(0) the controller sets the Service-Type attribute of a station's Access-Request to 'Framed'. By default this OID is set to 'disabled'. You cannot use RADIUS servers to authenticate administrators for local server access when this OID is set to 'enabled'.

applyMacAddressFormat.name: applyMacAddressFormat
applyMacAddressFormat.description: When this OID is set to enabled(1), the controller uses MAC-Based Authentication MAC address format (refer to radiusMacAddressFormatOption) for user authentication and accounting via RADIUS.

radiusExtnsSettingTable.name: radiusExtnsSettingTable
radiusExtnsSettingTable.description: List of RADIUS servers that will be used.

radiusExtnsSettingEntry.name: radiusExtnsSettingEntry
radiusExtnsSettingEntry.description: An entry for each RADIUS server.

radiusExtnsIndex.name: radiusExtnsIndex
radiusExtnsIndex.description: A number uniquely identifying each conceptual row in the radiusExtnsSettingTable. This value also equivalent to etsysRadiusAuthServerIndex of enterasys-radius-auth-client-mib.txt file.

pollingMechanism.name: pollingMechanism
pollingMechanism.description: This field specifies the method to determine the health of the RADIUS server. If set to useRFC5997StatusServerRequest(1), RFC 5997 Status-Server packets will be sent to the primary server to determine it's health. If set to authorizeAsActualUser(0), access-request messages for a specified user account will be sent to the primary server to determine it's health.

serverPollingInterval.name: serverPollingInterval
serverPollingInterval.description: Interval in seconds for the controller to poll the primary server.

netflowDestinationIP.name: netflowDestinationIP
netflowDestinationIP.description: The IP address for the Purview engine that will receive netflow records.

mirrorFirstN.name: mirrorFirstN
mirrorFirstN.description: If non-zero, the first N packets of a particular flow will be mirrored. If 0, all packets will be mirrored.

mirrorL2Ports.name: mirrorL2Ports
mirrorL2Ports.description: Configure the mirror port(s) on the controller. The default value is None. Only l2ports will be allowed to be selected and only when not referred to elsewhere (lag, topologies). The most significant bit of the most significant octet represents the first esa port (esa0). The second most significant bit of the most significant octet represents the second esa port (esa1) and so on.

radiusMacAddressFormatOption.name: radiusMacAddressFormatOption
radiusMacAddressFormatOption.description: The controller allows configuring different kinds of Mac address format in RADIUS messages. option1: mac address format as XXXXXXXXXXXX option2: mac address format as XX:XX:XX:XX:XX:XX option3: mac address format as XX-XX-XX-XX-XX-XX option4: mac address format as XXXX.XXXX.XXXX option5: mac address format as XXXXXX-XXXXXX option6: mac address format as XX XX XX XX XX XX option7: mac address format as xxxxxxxxxxxx option8: mac address format as xx:xx:xx:xx:xx:xx option9: mac address format as xx-xx-xx-xx-xx-xx option10: mac address format as xxxx.xxxx.xxxx option11: mac address format as xxxxxx-xxxxxx option12: mac address format as xx xx xx xx xx xx

wlanMaxEntries.name: wlanMaxEntries
wlanMaxEntries.description: Maximum number of WLAN supported by the device.

wlanNumEntries.name: wlanNumEntries
wlanNumEntries.description: The current number of entries in the wlanTable.

wlanTableNextAvailableIndex.name: wlanTableNextAvailableIndex
wlanTableNextAvailableIndex.description: This object indicates numerically lowest available index within this entity, which may be used for the value of index in the creation of new entry in wlanTable. An index is considered available if the index falls within the range of 1 to wlanMaxEntries and it is not being used to index an existing entry in the wlanTable contained this entity. This value should only be used as guideline for the management application and there is no requirement on the management application to create entries based upon this index value. Value of zero indicates there is no more room for new wlanTable creation.

wlanID.name: wlanID
wlanID.description: Unique internal ID associated with WLAN.

wlanRowStatus.name: wlanRowStatus
wlanRowStatus.description: This object allows dynamic creation and deletion of entries within wlanTable as well as activation and deactivation of these entries. For row creation, EWC only supports creatAndWait. WLAN name must be set before making the row active and persistent. Any WLAN that is associated to a VNS cannot be deleted unless it is first disassociated from VNS before being deleted. Any inactive entry will not be persistent and it will be lost during controller's restart.

wlanName.name: wlanName
wlanName.description: Text string uniquely identifying WLAN within EWC. Allowable characters for this field are from the set of A-Z, a-z, -!#$:, 0-9, and space. Howerver, it is recommended to avoid leading and trailing spaces.

wlanSSID.name: wlanSSID
wlanSSID.description: SSID (broadcast string) associated with WLAN. Allowable characters for this field are from the set of A-Z, a-z, _-.@, 0-9, and space. Howerver, it is recommendedto avoid leading and trailing spaces.

wlanSynchronize.name: wlanSynchronize
wlanSynchronize.description: If it is set to true, then WLAN will be replicated to peer controller if availability is configured and enabled.

wlanEnabled.name: wlanEnabled
wlanEnabled.description: This field is used to enable or disable this WLAN. If WLAN is disabled, then no traffic will be passed on behalf of this WLAN.

wlanDefaultTopologyID.name: wlanDefaultTopologyID
wlanDefaultTopologyID.description: The ID of topology from topologyTable associated to this WLAN. Topology ID of -1 means no default topology is associated to this WLAN. Physical topologies cannot be assigned to WLAN. The default topology indicates which topology to use for this WLAN if there is no topology associated with VNS via policy assignment.

wlanSessionTimeout.name: wlanSessionTimeout
wlanSessionTimeout.description: MU session that is associated to this WLAN will be terminated after elapse of this number of minutes from the start of its current session.

wlanIdleTimeoutPreAuth.name: wlanIdleTimeoutPreAuth
wlanIdleTimeoutPreAuth.description: Elapse time between association and authentication after which MU session will be terminated if the user is idle this amount of time without being authenticated.

wlanIdleSessionPostAuth.name: wlanIdleSessionPostAuth
wlanIdleSessionPostAuth.description: MU session that is associated to this WLAN will be terminated if the user is idle this amount of time after being authenticated.

wlanSupressSSID.name: wlanSupressSSID
wlanSupressSSID.description: If it is set to true then broadcast string (SSID) for this WLAN will not be broadcasted over the air.

wlanDot11hSupport.name: wlanDot11hSupport
wlanDot11hSupport.description: If it is set to true then dot11h support is enabled for clients associated to this WLAN.

wlanDot11hClientPowerReduction.name: wlanDot11hClientPowerReduction
wlanDot11hClientPowerReduction.description: If it is set to true then apply power reduction to dot11h clients associated to this WLAN. This field has meaning if wlanDot11hSupport is enabled (set to true).

wlanProcessClientIE.name: wlanProcessClientIE
wlanProcessClientIE.description: If it is set to true then clients that are associated to this WLAN their IE requests will be processed.

wlanEngerySaveMode.name: wlanEngerySaveMode
wlanEngerySaveMode.description: If it is set to true then engergy saving mode is enabled.

wlanBlockMuToMuTraffic.name: wlanBlockMuToMuTraffic
wlanBlockMuToMuTraffic.description: If it is set to true then two MU associated to this WLAN cannot communicate with each other.

wlanRemoteable.name: wlanRemoteable
wlanRemoteable.description: If it is set to true then this WLAN can be used as remote WLAN within mobility zone that this controller is partaking.

wlanVNSID.name: wlanVNSID
wlanVNSID.description: The ID of the VNS that uses this WLAN. WLAN can be created but not used in any VNS, in that case alue of zero indicates WLAN has not been used in any VNS. The value of this field set during VNS creation no during the WLAN creation.

wlanRadioManagement11k.name: wlanRadioManagement11k
wlanRadioManagement11k.description: When this bit is set to enable, the Radio Management (802.11k) feature is enabled on those APs who have this wlan configuration and 802.11k capability.

wlanBeaconReport.name: wlanBeaconReport
wlanBeaconReport.description: Enable/disable AP to send out beacon report. This field is configurable only if wlanRadioManagement11k is set to enable(1).

wlanQuietIE.name: wlanQuietIE
wlanQuietIE.description: Enable/disable AP to advertise a Quiet Element. This field is configurable only if wlanRadioManagement11k is set to enable(1).

wlanMirrorN.name: wlanMirrorN
wlanMirrorN.description: prohibited(0): Mirroring is prohibited. bothDirection(1) : Both direction packets will be mirrored. rxDirectionOnly(2): Only receive direction packets will be mirrored. Note: This will only take effect when the user's runtime current Roles's MirrorN action is None.

wlanNetFlow.name: wlanNetFlow
wlanNetFlow.description: Enable/disable netflow on this WLAN service.

wlanAppVisibility.name: wlanAppVisibility
wlanAppVisibility.description: Enable/disable both application visibility and control for this WLAN service.

wlanStatsTable.name: wlanStatsTable
wlanStatsTable.description: Stats related to WLAN (RFS) created on EWC.

wlanStatsEntry.name: wlanStatsEntry
wlanStatsEntry.description: An entery for each existing WLAN on EWC.

wlanStatsID.name: wlanStatsID
wlanStatsID.description: Unique internal ID associated with WLAN.

wlanStatsAssociatedClients.name: wlanStatsAssociatedClients
wlanStatsAssociatedClients.description: Number of clients that are currently associated to this WLAN.

wlanStatsRadiusTotRequests.name: wlanStatsRadiusTotRequests
wlanStatsRadiusTotRequests.description: Number of requests that were sent to RADIUS servers associated to this WLAN on behalf of MUs' requests using SSID associated to the WLAN for association, authentication or authorization to this WLAN.

wlanStatsRadiusReqFailed.name: wlanStatsRadiusReqFailed
wlanStatsRadiusReqFailed.description: Number of requests that were sent to RADIUS servers associated to this WLAN on behalf of MUs' requests for association, authentication or authorization to this WLAN but failed to be processed by RADIUS servers.

wlanStatsRadiusReqRejected.name: wlanStatsRadiusReqRejected
wlanStatsRadiusReqRejected.description: Number of requests that were sent to RADIUS servers associated to this WLAN on behalf of MUs' requests for association, authentication or authorization to this WLAN but rejected to be processed by RADIUS servers.

wlanPrivTable.name: wlanPrivTable
wlanPrivTable.description: This table contains configuration of privacy settings for all configured WLAN on EWC. For each of the configured WLAN on the controller one entry is added to this table. Addition/deletion of entries in this table are automatic depending on the addition or deletion of entries in wlanTable table.

wlanPrivEntry.name: wlanPrivEntry
wlanPrivEntry.description: An entry in wlanPrivTable for each configured WLAN on EWC. Each entry is indexed with corresponding wlan ID of wlanTable. The writable fields in this table can be modified depending on the corresponding wlanTable.

wlanPrivPrivacyType.name: wlanPrivPrivacyType
wlanPrivPrivacyType.description: Type of privacy applied to the corresponding configured WLAN. Configuration of the other fields in this table depends on the value of this field, e.g. if this field is set to none(0), then no other field in this table are settable.

wlanPrivWEPKeyIndex.name: wlanPrivWEPKeyIndex
wlanPrivWEPKeyIndex.description: Index of configured WEP. This field is required if and only if privacy type is staticWEP(1).

wlanPrivWEPKeyLength.name: wlanPrivWEPKeyLength
wlanPrivWEPKeyLength.description: Key legnth for the configured WEP key. This field is required if and only if privacy type is staticWEP(1).

wlanPrivWEPKey.name: wlanPrivWEPKey
wlanPrivWEPKey.description: The configured WEP key length must match the wlanPrivWEPKeyLength field. Any key with length longer or shorter than that length will be rejected. This field is required if and only if privacy type is staticWEP(1). This key can only be viewed in SNMPv3 mode with privacy.

wlanPrivWPAv1EncryptionType.name: wlanPrivWPAv1EncryptionType
wlanPrivWPAv1EncryptionType.description: The type of encryption used for WPA version 1 associations. This OID is undefined unless wlanPrivPrivacyType is wpa (3) or wpaPSK (4) and wlanPrivWPAversion is set to wpaV1 (1) or wpaV1andV2 (3).

wlanPrivWPAv2EncryptionType.name: wlanPrivWPAv2EncryptionType
wlanPrivWPAv2EncryptionType.description: The type of encryption used for WPA version 2 associations. This OID is undefined unless wlanPrivPrivacyType is wpa (3) or wpaPSK (4) and wlanPrivWPAversion is set to wpaV2 (2) or wpaV1 and V2 (3).

wlanPrivKeyManagement.name: wlanPrivKeyManagement
wlanPrivKeyManagement.description: Key management option available for the WPA2. This field has meaning if privacy type is WPA with WPA2 option enabled. This field can be modified only if wlanPrivPrivacyType is set to wpa(3) and wlanPrivWPAversion set to wpaV2(2) or wpaV1andV2(3). .

wlanPrivBroadcastRekeying.name: wlanPrivBroadcastRekeying
wlanPrivBroadcastRekeying.description: Broadcast rekeying if this value is set to true. This field can be modified only if wlanPrivPrivacyType is set to wpa(3) or wpaPSK(4).

wlanPrivRekeyInterval.name: wlanPrivRekeyInterval
wlanPrivRekeyInterval.description: Interval in seconds for requesting rekeying. This field has meaning if privacy type is WPA and broadcast rekeying is enabled (wlanPrivBroadcastRekeying is set to true). This field can be modified only if wlanPrivBroadcastRekeying is set to true.

wlanPrivGroupKPSR.name: wlanPrivGroupKPSR
wlanPrivGroupKPSR.description: Group Key Power Save Retry (GKPSR) value for the WPA type of privacy. This field can be modified only if wlanPrivPrivacyType is set to wpa(3) or wpaPSK(4).

wlanPrivWPAPSK.name: wlanPrivWPAPSK
wlanPrivWPAPSK.description: WPA-PSK shared key. This field has meaning if and only if WLAN privacy type is set to WPA-PSK. Input type can be either HEX formatted string or ASCII string. In case of HEX string, it must be 64 octets from set of hex characters. In case of ASCII string, the length is limited between 8 to 63 octets. This key can only be viewed in SNMPv3 mode with privacy. This field can be modified only if wlanPrivPrivacyType is set to wpaPSK(4).

wlanPrivWPAversion.name: wlanPrivWPAversion
wlanPrivWPAversion.description: Type of wpa version selected. This field can be modified only if wlanPrivPrivacyType is set to wpa(3) or wpaPSK(4). Note: wpa version v1 only is not allowed. 0 - no wpa version selected. 1 - wpa version v1 selected. 2 - wpa version v2 selected. 3 - both wpa version v1 and v2 selected.

wlanPrivfastTransition.name: wlanPrivfastTransition
wlanPrivfastTransition.description: When this field is set to enable(1), the 802.11r (fast transition) is enabled. This field can be modified only if wlanPrivPrivacyType is set to wpa(2).

wlanPrivManagementFrameProtection.name: wlanPrivManagementFrameProtection
wlanPrivManagementFrameProtection.description: Disable(0) : The AP will not encrypt any management frames. Enable(1): The AP will encrypt management frames for clients who also support this feature. If the clients do not support this feature, they are still able to connect to the AP but with no management frames encryption. Require(2): The AP will only allow clients who have the PMF feature to connect. Supported management frames will be encrypted to 802.11w standards. Clients who do not support this feature will not be able to associate.

wlanAuthTable.name: wlanAuthTable
wlanAuthTable.description: This table contains configuration of authentication settings for all configured WLAN on EWC. For each of the configured WLAN on the controller one entry is added to this table. Addition/deletion of entries in this table are automatic depending on the addition/deletion of entries in wlanTable table.

wlanAuthEntry.name: wlanAuthEntry
wlanAuthEntry.description: An entry in wlanAuthTable for each configured WLAN on EWC. Each entry is indexed with corresponding wlan ID of wlanTable. The writable fields in this table can be modified depending on the corresponding wlanTable. Note: All the fields in this table except wlanAuthType and wlanAuthCollectAcctInformation have meaning if MAC-based authentication filed (wlanAuthMacBasedAuth) is set to true.

wlanAuthType.name: wlanAuthType
wlanAuthType.description: The type of authentication applied to stations attempting to associate to a BSSID belonging to this WLAN Service. If the dot1x type is selected, then this WLAN must have privacy. When the dot1x or internalCP is selected, the controller must have a RADIUS server, and SNMP will auto assign one RADIUS server to this WLAN if the user did not assign one.

wlanAuthMacBasedAuth.name: wlanAuthMacBasedAuth
wlanAuthMacBasedAuth.description: MAC based authorization is enabled if this field is set to true. When this field set to true, SNMP will auto configure one RADIUS server to enable MAC authorization.

wlanAuthMACBasedAuthOnRoam.name: wlanAuthMACBasedAuthOnRoam
wlanAuthMACBasedAuthOnRoam.description: If it is set to true, the client will be forced to go through MAC based authorization when the client roamed. This field has meaning only when wlanAuthMacBasedAuth is set to true. This field can be modified only when wlanAuthMacBasedAuth is set to true.

wlanAuthAutoAuthAuthorizedUser.name: wlanAuthAutoAuthAuthorizedUser
wlanAuthAutoAuthAuthorizedUser.description: All authorized users will be considered authenticated automatically. This field has meaning only when wlanAuthMacBasedAuth is set to true. This field can be modified only when wlanAuthMacBasedAuth is set to true.

wlanAuthAllowUnauthorizedUser.name: wlanAuthAllowUnauthorizedUser
wlanAuthAllowUnauthorizedUser.description: Unauthorized users will be allowed if this field is set to true.This field has meaning only when wlanAuthMacBasedAuth is set to true. This field can be modified only when wlanAuthMacBasedAuth is set to true.

wlanAuthRadiusIncludeAP.name: wlanAuthRadiusIncludeAP
wlanAuthRadiusIncludeAP.description: AP serial number will be included in RADIUS request packet as VSA if this field is set to true.

wlanAuthRadiusIncludeVNS.name: wlanAuthRadiusIncludeVNS
wlanAuthRadiusIncludeVNS.description: VNS name will be included in RADIUS request packet as VSA if this field is set to true.

wlanAuthRadiusIncludeSSID.name: wlanAuthRadiusIncludeSSID
wlanAuthRadiusIncludeSSID.description: WLAN SSID will be included in RADIUS request packet as VSA if this field is set to true.

wlanAuthRadiusIncludePolicy.name: wlanAuthRadiusIncludePolicy
wlanAuthRadiusIncludePolicy.description: Policy name will be included in RADIUS request packet as VSA if this field is set to true.

wlanAuthRadiusIncludeTopology.name: wlanAuthRadiusIncludeTopology
wlanAuthRadiusIncludeTopology.description: Topology name will be included in RADIUS request packet as VSA if this field is set to true.

wlanAuthRadiusIncludeIngressRC.name: wlanAuthRadiusIncludeIngressRC
wlanAuthRadiusIncludeIngressRC.description: Ingress rate control name will be included in RADIUS request packet as VSA if this field is set to true.

wlanAuthRadiusIncludeEgressRC.name: wlanAuthRadiusIncludeEgressRC
wlanAuthRadiusIncludeEgressRC.description: Egress rate control name will be included in RADIUS request packet as VSA if this field is set to true.

wlanAuthCollectAcctInformation.name: wlanAuthCollectAcctInformation
wlanAuthCollectAcctInformation.description: Accounting information is collected for clients if this field is set to true.

wlanAuthReplaceCalledStationIDWithZone.name: wlanAuthReplaceCalledStationIDWithZone
wlanAuthReplaceCalledStationIDWithZone.description: Replace called station ID with Zone if this field is set to true.

wlanAuthRadiusAcctAfterMacBaseAuthorizat.name: wlanAuthRadiusAcctAfterMacBaseAuthorization
wlanAuthRadiusAcctAfterMacBaseAuthorizat.description: RADIUS accounting begins after MAC-based authorization completes if this field is set to true. This field has meaning only when wlanAuthMacBasedAuth is set to true. This field can be modified only when wlanAuthMacBasedAuth is set to true.

wlanAuthRadiusTimeoutRole.name: wlanAuthRadiusTimeoutRole
wlanAuthRadiusTimeoutRole.description: Apply this role to clients when the RADIUS server timed out. '-1' is treat like access reject. Any other number is the Role ID. This field has meaning only when wlanAuthMacBasedAuth is set to true. This field can be modified only when wlanAuthMacBasedAuth is set to true.

wlanAuthRadiusOperatorNameSpace.name: wlanAuthRadiusOperatorNameSpace
wlanAuthRadiusOperatorNameSpace.description: wlanAuthRadiusOperatorNameSpace is the Namespace ID as defined in RFC 5580. The value within this field contains the operator namespace identifier. The Namespace ID value is encoded in ASCII and has the following values. -1 : disabled. 48 : TADIG. 49 : REALM. 50 : E212. 51 : ICC.

wlanAuthRadiusOperatorName.name: wlanAuthRadiusOperatorName
wlanAuthRadiusOperatorName.description: RADIUS accounting message will include this string when the wlanAuthRadiusOperatorNameSpace is not set to -1.

wlanAuthMACBasedAuthReAuthOnAreaRoam.name: wlanAuthMACBasedAuthReAuthOnAreaRoam
wlanAuthMACBasedAuthReAuthOnAreaRoam.description: If this field is set to true, the client will be forced to go through MAC based authorization when the client roams to another area. This field has meaning and can be modified only when wlanAuthMacBasedAuth is set to true.

wlanRadiusTable.name: wlanRadiusTable
wlanRadiusTable.description: This table contains configuration of RADIUS settings for all configured WLAN on EWC. For each of the configured WLAN on the controller there may exist one or more entries of RADIUS server(s) serving the WLAN. Addition/deletion of entries in this table are automatic depending on the addition/deletion of entries in wlanTable table.

wlanRadiusEntry.name: wlanRadiusEntry
wlanRadiusEntry.description: An entry in wlanRadiusTable for each RADIUS server used by the WLAN indexed by wlanID.

wlanRadiusIndex.name: wlanRadiusIndex
wlanRadiusIndex.description: Internally generated index and it has no external meaning.

wlanRadiusName.name: wlanRadiusName
wlanRadiusName.description: Name of the RADIUS server associated to this entry.

wlanRadiusUsage.name: wlanRadiusUsage
wlanRadiusUsage.description: Usage type associated to this entry for authentication.

wlanRadiusPriority.name: wlanRadiusPriority
wlanRadiusPriority.description: Priority associated to this entry for authentication. RADIUS servers are contacted for authentication requests in the order of their priority defined in this field. The highest priority servers (priorities with lower numerical values have higher priority order) are consulted first for any authentication request.

wlanRadiusPort.name: wlanRadiusPort
wlanRadiusPort.description: The RADIUS authentication requests should be sent to this authentication port.

wlanRadiusRetries.name: wlanRadiusRetries
wlanRadiusRetries.description: Maximum number of retries attempted for an specific authentication request.

wlanRadiusTimeout.name: wlanRadiusTimeout
wlanRadiusTimeout.description: Number of seconds to wait for a response from authentication server for each request sent to the server before considering the request as failure.

wlanRadiusNASUseVnsIP.name: wlanRadiusNASUseVnsIP
wlanRadiusNASUseVnsIP.description: If this value is set to true, then VNS IP address associated to the WLAN indexed by wlanID to this entry is used as NAS IP address. Otherwise NAS IP address should be configured manually.

wlanRadiusNASIP.name: wlanRadiusNASIP
wlanRadiusNASIP.description: NAS IP associated to this RADIUS server. Configuration of this field is directly affected by the value of wlanRadiusNASUseVnsIP.

wlanRadiusNASIDUseVNSName.name: wlanRadiusNASIDUseVNSName
wlanRadiusNASIDUseVNSName.description: If this value is set to true, then use VNS name associated to the WLAN indexed by wlanID for this entry as NAS ID. Otherwise NAS ID should be configured manually.

wlanRadiusNASID.name: wlanRadiusNASID
wlanRadiusNASID.description: NAS ID associated to this RADIUS server. Configuration of this field is directly affected by the value of wlanRadiusNASIDUseVNSName.

wlanRadiusAuthType.name: wlanRadiusAuthType
wlanRadiusAuthType.description: Authentication type used for this WLAN when using this RADIUS server to authenticate users.

wlanCPTable.name: wlanCPTable
wlanCPTable.description: This table contains configuration of Captive Portal settings for all configured WLAN on EWC. For each of the configured WLAN on the controller one entry is added to this table. Addition/deletion of entries in this table are automatic depending on the addition/deletion of entries in wlanTable table. This table can be accessed using SNMPv3 on behalf of users with privacy.

wlanCPEntry.name: wlanCPEntry
wlanCPEntry.description: An entry in wlanCPTable for each configured WLAN on EWC. Each entry is indexed with corresponding wlan ID of wlanTable. The writable fields in this table can be modified depending on the corresponding wlanTable and type of CP assigned to the WLAN. If the authentication type is 'disabled(0)' for the WLAN, then all other entries in this table have no meaning.

wlanCPAuthType.name: wlanCPAuthType
wlanCPAuthType.description: Type of authentication applied to MU requesting association using SSID associated to this WLAN.

wlanCP802HttpRedirect.name: wlanCP802HttpRedirect
wlanCP802HttpRedirect.description: If it is set to true, then CP will be redirected to configured CP. This value has meaning only for CP of the type 'dot1x(3)'.

wlanCPExtConnection.name: wlanCPExtConnection
wlanCPExtConnection.description: IP address of the interface for this CP.

wlanCPExtPort.name: wlanCPExtPort
wlanCPExtPort.description: The port associated to the CP IP address.

wlanCPExtEnableHttps.name: wlanCPExtEnableHttps
wlanCPExtEnableHttps.description: HTTPS support is enabled if this field is set to true.

wlanCPExtEncryption.name: wlanCPExtEncryption
wlanCPExtEncryption.description: Type of encryption for the CP.

wlanCPExtSharedSecret.name: wlanCPExtSharedSecret
wlanCPExtSharedSecret.description: Shared secret used for this captive portal.

wlanCPExtTosOverride.name: wlanCPExtTosOverride
wlanCPExtTosOverride.description: Override ToS of NAC server usage only.

wlanCPExtTosValue.name: wlanCPExtTosValue
wlanCPExtTosValue.description: ToS value for NAC server only.

wlanCPExtAddIPtoURL.name: wlanCPExtAddIPtoURL
wlanCPExtAddIPtoURL.description: If this value is set to true, then add EWC IP address and port number to the redirection URL.

wlanCPIntLogoffButton.name: wlanCPIntLogoffButton
wlanCPIntLogoffButton.description: If set to true provide 'Logoff' button to the user in CP page.

wlanCPIntStatusCheckButton.name: wlanCPIntStatusCheckButton
wlanCPIntStatusCheckButton.description: If set to true provide 'Status Check' button to the user in CP page.

wlanCPReplaceIPwithFQDN.name: wlanCPReplaceIPwithFQDN
wlanCPReplaceIPwithFQDN.description: Replace CP gateway IP address with FQDN.

wlanCPSendLoginTo.name: wlanCPSendLoginTo
wlanCPSendLoginTo.description: This field indicates to what URL the successful login session must be redirected. This field qualifies wlanCPRedirectURL.

wlanCPRedirectURL.name: wlanCPRedirectURL
wlanCPRedirectURL.description: Text string identifying default redirection URL.

wlanCPGuestAccLifetime.name: wlanCPGuestAccLifetime
wlanCPGuestAccLifetime.description: This value indicates for how many days the guest account is valid. Value of zero indicates that there is no limit for the guest account.

wlanCPGuestAllowedLifetimeAcct.name: wlanCPGuestAllowedLifetimeAcct
wlanCPGuestAllowedLifetimeAcct.description: If this value is set to true, then guest admin can obtain lifetime account.

wlanCPGuestSessionLifetime.name: wlanCPGuestSessionLifetime
wlanCPGuestSessionLifetime.description: The guess account session using this CP cannot last longer than this number of hours. Value of zero means there is no limit for the session.

wlanCPGuestIDPrefix.name: wlanCPGuestIDPrefix
wlanCPGuestIDPrefix.description: The prefix used for guest portal user ID label.

wlanCPGuestMinPassLength.name: wlanCPGuestMinPassLength
wlanCPGuestMinPassLength.description: Minimum password length for the guest user account associated to this WLAN.

wlanCPGuestMaxConcurrentSession.name: wlanCPGuestMaxConcurrentSession
wlanCPGuestMaxConcurrentSession.description: Maximum number of the guest users can use this set of credentials to access this concurrent session.

wlanCPUseHTTPSforConnection.name: wlanCPUseHTTPSforConnection
wlanCPUseHTTPSforConnection.description: When this value set to true, use HTTPS for user connection. It has meaning only when wlanCPAuthType is set to internalCP(2) or easyGuestCP(5) or guestSplash(6)

wlanCPIdentity.name: wlanCPIdentity
wlanCPIdentity.description: wlanCPIdentity is used to identify the EWC to the external captive portal server (ECP) and the ECP to the EWC.

wlanCPCustomSpecificURL.name: wlanCPCustomSpecificURL
wlanCPCustomSpecificURL.description: After a user successfully logs in, the user will be redirected to the URL as defined in the wlanCPCustomSpecificURL.

wlanCPSelectionOption.name: wlanCPSelectionOption
wlanCPSelectionOption.description: Append the above parameter(s) to the EWC captive portal redirection URL if one or more of the bits are set.

wlanUnsecuredWlanCounts.name: wlanUnsecuredWlanCounts
wlanUnsecuredWlanCounts.description: Total number of WLAN with security issues. The details of security issues can be found in wlanSecurityReportTable.

wlanSecurityReportTable.name: wlanSecurityReportTable
wlanSecurityReportTable.description: This table contains the weak configuration settings for all configured WLAN on EWC. For each of the configured WLAN on the controller there exist one entry in this table. Addition/deletion of entries in this table are automatic depending on the addition or deletion of entries in wlanTable table. This table can be accessed using SNMPv3 on behalf of users with privacy.

wlanSecurityReportEntry.name: wlanSecurityReportEntry
wlanSecurityReportEntry.description: An entry in wlanSecurityReportTable for each configured WLAN on EWC. Each entry is indexed with corresponding wlan ID of wlanTable.

wlanSecurityReportFlag.name: wlanSecurityReportFlag
wlanSecurityReportFlag.description: Value of secureSetting(2) indicates that WLAN has secure configuration.

wlanSecurityReportUnsecureType.name: wlanSecurityReportUnsecureType
wlanSecurityReportUnsecureType.description: bit 0: by setting this bit means this WLAN does not use any kind of encryption bit 1: by setting this bit means this WLAN uses weak WEP encryption bit 2: by setting this bit means this WLAN uses weak tkip encryption bit 3: by setting this bit means this WLAN uses default SSID bit 4: by setting this bit means this WLAN uses HotSpot SSID bit 5: by setting this bit means this WLAN uses Rainbow SSID bit 6: by setting this bit means this WLAN uses dictionary word as an encryption key bit 7: by setting this bit means this WLAN uses dictionary word in an encryption key string bit 8: by setting this bit means this WLAN uses a short password key

wlanSecurityReportNotes.name: wlanSecurityReportNotes
wlanSecurityReportNotes.description: Textual description of any security issues related to the WLAN is reflected in this field.

wlanRadiusServerTable.name: wlanRadiusServerTable
wlanRadiusServerTable.description: This table contains configuration of RADIUS Servers settings for all configured WLANs on the Wireless Controller. For each of the configured WLANs on the controller there may exist one or more entries of RADIUS server(s) serving the WLAN. Addition/deletion of entries in this table are automatic depending on the addition/deletion of entries in wlanTable table.

wlanRadiusServerEntry.name: wlanRadiusServerEntry
wlanRadiusServerEntry.description: An entry in wlanRadiusServerTable for each RADIUS server used by the WLAN indexed by wlanID and radiusId. The radiusId is the controller's internal radius server index.

wlanRadiusServerUse.name: wlanRadiusServerUse
wlanRadiusServerUse.description: use : This means that this WLAN service indexed by wlanID uses this RADIUS server which it is indexed by the radiusId.

wlanRadiusServerUsage.name: wlanRadiusServerUsage
wlanRadiusServerUsage.description: bit 0: By setting this bit, this RADIUS server is used for authentication. This bit has meaning only when wlanAuthType is set to internalCP(2), dot1x(3), or externalCP(4). bit 1: By setting this bit, this RADIUS server is used for MAC-based authentication. This bit has meaning only when wlanAuthMacBasedAuth is set to true. bit 2: By setting this bit, this RADIUS server is used for accounting. This bit has meaning only when wlanAuthType is set to internalCP(2), dot1x(3), or externalCP(4).

wlanRadiusServerAuthUseVNSIPAddr.name: wlanRadiusServerAuthUseVNSIPAddr
wlanRadiusServerAuthUseVNSIPAddr.description: When this value set to true, use the VNS's IP address as NAS IP address during the authentication.

wlanRadiusServerAuthNASIP.name: wlanRadiusServerAuthNASIP
wlanRadiusServerAuthNASIP.description: Use this IP address as the NAS IP addresss during the authentication. The default IP address is the VNS IP address. This field has meaning only when the wlanRadiusServerUsage's bit 0 is set.

wlanRadiusServerAuthUseVNSName.name: wlanRadiusServerAuthUseVNSName
wlanRadiusServerAuthUseVNSName.description: When this value set to true, use the VNS's name as the NAS identifier during the authentication.

wlanRadiusServerAuthNASId.name: wlanRadiusServerAuthNASId
wlanRadiusServerAuthNASId.description: Use this name as the NAS identifier during the authentication. The default name is the VNS name. This field has meaning only when the wlanRadiusServerUsage's bit 0 is set.

wlanRadiusServerAuthAuthType.name: wlanRadiusServerAuthAuthType
wlanRadiusServerAuthAuthType.description: Authentication type. This field has meaning only when the wlanRadiusServerUsage's bit 0 is set.

wlanRadiusServerAcctUseVNSIPAddr.name: wlanRadiusServerAcctUseVNSIPAddr
wlanRadiusServerAcctUseVNSIPAddr.description: When this value set to true, use the VNS's IP address as NAS IP address during the accounting.

wlanRadiusServerAcctNASIP.name: wlanRadiusServerAcctNASIP
wlanRadiusServerAcctNASIP.description: Use this IP address as the NAS IP addresss during the accounting. The default IP address is the VNS IP address. This field has meaning only when the wlanRadiusServerUsage's bit 2 is set.

wlanRadiusServerAcctUseVNSName.name: wlanRadiusServerAcctUseVNSName
wlanRadiusServerAcctUseVNSName.description: When this value set to true, use the VNS's name as the NAS identifier during the accounting.

wlanRadiusServerAcctNASId.name: wlanRadiusServerAcctNASId
wlanRadiusServerAcctNASId.description: Use this name as the NAS identifier during the accounting. The default name is the VNS name. This field has meaning only when the wlanRadiusServerUsage's bit 2 is set.

wlanRadiusServerAcctSIAR.name: wlanRadiusServerAcctSIAR
wlanRadiusServerAcctSIAR.description: If this value is set to true, then the controller sends interrim accounting records for fast failover events. This field has meaning only when the wlanRadiusServerUsage's bit 2 is set.

wlanRadiusServerMacUseVNSIPAddr.name: wlanRadiusServerMacUseVNSIPAddr
wlanRadiusServerMacUseVNSIPAddr.description: When this value set to true, use the VNS's IP address as NAS IP address during the MAC based authentication.

wlanRadiusServerMacNASIP.name: wlanRadiusServerMacNASIP
wlanRadiusServerMacNASIP.description: Use this IP address as the NAS IP addresss during the MAC based authentication. The default IP address is the VNS IP address. This field has meaning only when the wlanRadiusServerUsage's bit 1 is set.

wlanRadiusServerMacUseVNSName.name: wlanRadiusServerMacUseVNSName
wlanRadiusServerMacUseVNSName.description: When this value set to true, use the VNS's name as the NAS identifier during the MAC based authentication.

wlanRadiusServerMacNASId.name: wlanRadiusServerMacNASId
wlanRadiusServerMacNASId.description: Use this name as the NAS identifier during the MAC based authentication. The default name is the VNS name. This field has meaning only when the wlanRadiusServerUsage's bit 1 is set.

wlanRadiusServerMacAuthType.name: wlanRadiusServerMacAuthType
wlanRadiusServerMacAuthType.description: Authentication type. This field has meaning only when the wlanRadiusServerUsage's bit 1 is set.

wlanRadiusServerMacPW.name: wlanRadiusServerMacPW
wlanRadiusServerMacPW.description: The password is used for MAC based authentication. This field has meaning only when the wlanRadiusServerUsage's bit 1 is set.

topologyTable.name: topologyTable
topologyTable.description: List of topologies configured on EWC.

topologyEntry.name: topologyEntry
topologyEntry.description: Configuration information about a topology in topology table. EWC supports different types of topologies, therefore, for complete configuration of a topology not all fields are necessary to be defined or have meaning. Definition of each field in this table specifies topolog-specific characteristics of the field and its relevance.

topologyID.name: topologyID
topologyID.description: Unique internal identifier of the topology. This item is generated internally by EWC and has no external meaning.

topologyName.name: topologyName
topologyName.description: Name associated with topology. This name must be unique within EWC. Allowable characters for this field are from the set of A-Z, a-z, -!#$:, 0-9, and space. Howerver, it is recommended to avoid leading and trailing spaces.

topologyMode.name: topologyMode
topologyMode.description: Type of this topology. This field implies the meaning and necessity of other attributes associated to the topology.

topologyTagged.name: topologyTagged
topologyTagged.description: If topology is tagged, then a VLAN ID must be assigned to the topology. Meaning associated to this field is topology specific: - For Admin topology (management port) is always untagged - Ror routed topology has no meaning and always untagged - For all other topologies this field is configurable.

topologyVlanID.name: topologyVlanID
topologyVlanID.description: VLAN ID assigned to a tagged topology. For untagged topology this field has no meaning and it is set to -1.

topologyEgressPort.name: topologyEgressPort
topologyEgressPort.description: Egress port associated to this topology if it is tagged and VLANID defined for the topology. This field is represented as octect string: The most significant bit of most significant octet represent first physical port (lowest number port) and second most significant bit of most significant octet represent second physical port and so on. Meaning associated to this field is topology specific: - For Admin topology (management port) this field has no meaning. - Ror routed topology this field has no meaning - For all other topologies: physical, bridge at controller, and bridge at AP topologies this field is configurable.

topologyLayer3.name: topologyLayer3
topologyLayer3.description: If set to true, then topology has layer three persence. Any topology with layer three presence must have IP address and gateway assigned to it. Meaning associated to this field is topology specific: - For Admin topology (management port) it is always set to true. - Ror bridge at AP this field has no meaning and it is set to false. - For routed and physical topologies it is always set to true. - For bridge at controller type of topology this field is configurable.

topologyIPAddress.name: topologyIPAddress
topologyIPAddress.description: IP address assigned to the topology as its interface. Meaning associated to this field is topology specific: - This field has meaning if topology has layer three presence. - Ror bridge at AP this field has no meaning and set 0.0.0.0.

topologyIPMask.name: topologyIPMask
topologyIPMask.description: Mask for topology's IP address. This field is only applicable to those topologies that have IP address assigned to them, otherwise it is set either to 255.255.255.255 or 0.0.0.0.

topologyMTUsize.name: topologyMTUsize
topologyMTUsize.description: Default MTU size for the topology. This field is only configurable for a topologies that has layer three presence.

topologyGateway.name: topologyGateway
topologyGateway.description: Gateway associated to this topology. This field has meaning for a topology that has layer three presence.

topologyDHCPUsage.name: topologyDHCPUsage
topologyDHCPUsage.description: The type of DHCP to be used for IP address assignment to associated MU. This field has meaning only if the topology has layer three persense. Meaning associated to this field is topology specific: - For Admin topology (management port) has no meaning. - Ror bridge at AP this field has no meaning. - For all other topologies that their layer three presence is enabled this field is configurable.

topologyAPRegistration.name: topologyAPRegistration
topologyAPRegistration.description: If set to true, then AP registration can be achieved using via this topology. Meaning associated to this field is topology specific: - Always false for Admin (management port) and routed topologies - Always false and has no meaning for bridge at AP topology. - For physical and bridge at controller type topologies that have layer three presence this field can be set to either true or false.

topologyManagementTraffic.name: topologyManagementTraffic
topologyManagementTraffic.description: If set to true, then management data traffic is allowed on this topology. Meaning associated to this field is topology specific: - Always true for Admin topology (management port) - Has no meaning for bridge at AP type topologies - For all other topologies that have layer three presence this field can be set to either true or false.

topologySynchronize.name: topologySynchronize
topologySynchronize.description: If set to true, then topology must be synchronized with peer controller in availability mode operation. Meaning associated to this field is topology specific: - Always false for Admin topology (management port) - Has no meaning for topologies associated to physical ports. - For all other topologies: bridge at controller, routed and bridge at AP type topologies this field can be set to either true or false.

topologySyncGateway.name: topologySyncGateway
topologySyncGateway.description: Gateway associated to synchronized topology. This field has meaning for those topologies that their topologySynchornize field is set to true.

topologySyncMask.name: topologySyncMask
topologySyncMask.description: Mask of synchronized gateway IP address. This field has meaning for those topologies that their topologySynchornize field is set to true.

topologySyncIPStart.name: topologySyncIPStart
topologySyncIPStart.description: Range of IP addresses assigned to remote synchronized topology. This IP address represents starting IP address. This field has meaning for those topologies that their topologySynchornize field is set to true.

topologySyncIPEnd.name: topologySyncIPEnd
topologySyncIPEnd.description: Range of IP addresses assigned to remote synchronized topology. This IP address represents ending IP address. This field has meaning for those topologies that their topologySynchornize field is set to true.

topologyStaticIPv6Address.name: topologyStaticIPv6Address
topologyStaticIPv6Address.description: Statically configured IPv6 address assigned to the admin port.

topologyLinkLocalIPv6Address.name: topologyLinkLocalIPv6Address
topologyLinkLocalIPv6Address.description: Automatically generated link-local IPv6 address assigned to the admin port.

topologyPreFixLength.name: topologyPreFixLength
topologyPreFixLength.description: The prfix length of the statically configured IPv6 address of the topology.

topologyIPv6Gateway.name: topologyIPv6Gateway
topologyIPv6Gateway.description: The gateway of IPv6 address that is associated to the admin topology.

topologyDynamicEgress.name: topologyDynamicEgress
topologyDynamicEgress.description: Enable/disable dynamic egress for this topology. Dynamic egress allows a station to receive from this VLAN if it can send to this VLAN.

topologyIsGroup.name: topologyIsGroup
topologyIsGroup.description: When this flag is yes, this means the topology is created as a group topology.

topologyGroupMembers.name: topologyGroupMembers
topologyGroupMembers.description: This field specifies the topologies for this group. This field has meaning only when topologyIsGroup is set to 1. This field is represented as octect string. The most significant bit of the most significant octet of the octet string represents the first topology with topologyID = 0 and second most significant bit of the most significant octet represents the second topology with topologyID = 1 and so on.

topologyMemberId.name: topologyMemberId
topologyMemberId.description: -1 : Means this topology is not a member of a group topology. valid topology ID : Means this topology is a member of a configured group topology that has this group topology ID.

topoStatTable.name: topoStatTable
topoStatTable.description: Statistics describing traffic transmitted or received for a single topology. This is the traffic on the topology that is coming from or going to destinations on the wired network.

topoStatEntry.name: topoStatEntry
topoStatEntry.description: Statistic related an entry in topology table.

topoStatTxPkts.name: topoStatTxPkts
topoStatTxPkts.description: Number of packets transmitted to the wired network on the topology/vlan.

topoStatRxPkts.name: topoStatRxPkts
topoStatRxPkts.description: Number of packets received from the wired network on the topology/vlan.

topoStatTxOctets.name: topoStatTxOctets
topoStatTxOctets.description: Number of octets transmitted in frames to the wired network on the topology/vlan.

topoStatRxOctets.name: topoStatRxOctets
topoStatRxOctets.description: Number of octets received in frames from the wired network on the topology/vlan.

topoStatMulticastTxPkts.name: topoStatMulticastTxPkts
topoStatMulticastTxPkts.description: Number of multicast frames transmitted to the wired network on the topology/vlan.

topoStatMulticastRxPkts.name: topoStatMulticastRxPkts
topoStatMulticastRxPkts.description: Number of multicast frames received from the wired network on the topology/vlan.

topoStatBroadcastTxPkts.name: topoStatBroadcastTxPkts
topoStatBroadcastTxPkts.description: Number of broadcast frames transmitted to the wired network on the topology/vlan.

topoStatBroadcastRxPkts.name: topoStatBroadcastRxPkts
topoStatBroadcastRxPkts.description: Number of broadcast frames received from the wired network on the topology/vlan.

topoStatFrameChkSeqErrors.name: topoStatFrameChkSeqErrors
topoStatFrameChkSeqErrors.description: Number of frames with checksum errors received from the wired network on the topology/vlan.

topoStatFrameTooLongErrors.name: topoStatFrameTooLongErrors
topoStatFrameTooLongErrors.description: Number of oversized frames received from the wired network on the topology/vlan.

topoExceptionStatTable.name: topoExceptionStatTable
topoExceptionStatTable.description: The table contains list of exception-specific filters statistics for configured topologies in EWC.

topoExceptionStatEntry.name: topoExceptionStatEntry
topoExceptionStatEntry.description: An entry in topology exception statistic table.

topoExceptionStatPktsDenied.name: topoExceptionStatPktsDenied
topoExceptionStatPktsDenied.description: Number of packets that were denied by defined filters since device's last restart.

topoExceptionStatPktsAllowed.name: topoExceptionStatPktsAllowed
topoExceptionStatPktsAllowed.description: Number packets that were allowed by defined filters since device's last restart.

topoWireStatTable.name: topoWireStatTable
topoWireStatTable.description: The table contains statistics describing traffic transmitted or received unencapsulated (i.e. not wrapped in WASSP) for each topology

topoWireStatEntry.name: topoWireStatEntry
topoWireStatEntry.description: Statistics describing traffic transmitted or received unencapsulated (i.e. not wrapped in WASSP) for a single topology. This is the traffic on the topology that is coming from or going to destinations on the wired network other than to the controller's APs.

topoWireStatTxPkts.name: topoWireStatTxPkts
topoWireStatTxPkts.description: Number of packets transmitted unencapsulated to the wired network on the topology/vlan.

topoWireStatRxPkts.name: topoWireStatRxPkts
topoWireStatRxPkts.description: Number of packets received unencapsulated from the wired network on the topology/vlan.

topoWireStatTxOctets.name: topoWireStatTxOctets
topoWireStatTxOctets.description: Number of octets transmitted in unencapsulated frames to the wired network on the topology/vlan.

topoWireStatRxOctets.name: topoWireStatRxOctets
topoWireStatRxOctets.description: Number of octets received in unencapsulated frames to the wired network on the topology/vlan.

topoWireStatMulticastTxPkts.name: topoWireStatMulticastTxPkts
topoWireStatMulticastTxPkts.description: Number of multicast frames transmitted unencapsulated to the wired network on the topology/vlan.

topoWireStatMulticastRxPkts.name: topoWireStatMulticastRxPkts
topoWireStatMulticastRxPkts.description: Number of multicast frames received unencapsulated from the wired network on the topology/vlan.

topoWireStatBroadcastTxPkts.name: topoWireStatBroadcastTxPkts
topoWireStatBroadcastTxPkts.description: Number of broadcast frames transmitted unencapsulated to the wired network on the topology/vlan.

topoWireStatBroadcastRxPkts.name: topoWireStatBroadcastRxPkts
topoWireStatBroadcastRxPkts.description: Number of broadcast frames received unencapsulated from the wired network on the topology/vlan.

topoWireStatFrameChkSeqErrors.name: topoWireStatFrameChkSeqErrors
topoWireStatFrameChkSeqErrors.description: Number of unencapsulated frames with checksum errors received from the wired network on the topology/vlan.

topoWireStatFrameTooLongErrors.name: topoWireStatFrameTooLongErrors
topoWireStatFrameTooLongErrors.description: Number of unencapsulated frames with length longer than permitted received from the wired network on the topology/vlan.

topoCompleteStatTable.name: topoCompleteStatTable
topoCompleteStatTable.description: The table contains statistics describing traffic transmitted and received for each topology on both the wired side and the wireless side.

topoCompleteStatEntry.name: topoCompleteStatEntry
topoCompleteStatEntry.description: Statistics describing traffic transmitted and received on a single topology on both the wired side and the wireless side.

topoCompleteStatTxPkts.name: topoCompleteStatTxPkts
topoCompleteStatTxPkts.description: Number of packets transmitted to the wired and wireless networks on the topology/vlan.

topoCompleteStatRxPkts.name: topoCompleteStatRxPkts
topoCompleteStatRxPkts.description: Number of packets received from the wired and wireless networks on the topology/vlan.

topoCompleteStatTxOctets.name: topoCompleteStatTxOctets
topoCompleteStatTxOctets.description: Number of octets transmitted in frames to the wired and wireless networks on the topology/vlan.

topoCompleteStatRxOctets.name: topoCompleteStatRxOctets
topoCompleteStatRxOctets.description: Number of octets received in frames from the wired and wireless networks on the topology/vlan.

topoCompleteStatMulticastTxPkts.name: topoCompleteStatMulticastTxPkts
topoCompleteStatMulticastTxPkts.description: Number of multicast frames transmitted to the wired and wireless networks on the topology/vlan.

topoCompleteStatMulticastRxPkts.name: topoCompleteStatMulticastRxPkts
topoCompleteStatMulticastRxPkts.description: Number of multicast frames received from the wired and wireless networks on the topology/vlan.

topoCompleteStatBroadcastTxPkts.name: topoCompleteStatBroadcastTxPkts
topoCompleteStatBroadcastTxPkts.description: Number of broadcast frames transmitted to the wired and wireless networks on the topology/vlan.

topoCompleteStatBroadcastRxPkts.name: topoCompleteStatBroadcastRxPkts
topoCompleteStatBroadcastRxPkts.description: Number of broadcast frames received from the wired and wireless networks on the topology/vlan.

topoCompleteStatFrameChkSeqErrors.name: topoCompleteStatFrameChkSeqErrors
topoCompleteStatFrameChkSeqErrors.description: Number of frames with checksum errors received from the wired and wireless networks on the topology/vlan.

topoCompleteStatFrameTooLongErrors.name: topoCompleteStatFrameTooLongErrors
topoCompleteStatFrameTooLongErrors.description: Number of oversized frames received from the wired and wireless networks on the topology/vlan.

apCount.name: apCount
apCount.description: The count of currently configured AccessPoints associated with this WirelessController.

apTable.name: apTable
apTable.description: Contains a list of all configured APs associated with the Wireless Controller.

apEntry.name: apEntry
apEntry.description: Configuration information for an access point.

apIndex.name: apIndex
apIndex.description: Table index for the access point.

apPortifIndex.name: apPortifIndex
apPortifIndex.description: ifIndex of the physical port to which this AP is assigned.

apWiredIfIndex.name: apWiredIfIndex
apWiredIfIndex.description: ifIndex of the wired interface on the AP.

apSoftwareVersion.name: apSoftwareVersion
apSoftwareVersion.description: Software version currently installed on the AP.

apSpecific.name: apSpecific
apSpecific.description: A link back to the OID under the hiPathWirelessProducts branch that identifies the specific version of this AP.

apBroadcastDisassociate.name: apBroadcastDisassociate
apBroadcastDisassociate.description: True indicates that the AP should broadcast disassociation requests, False indicates unicast.

apVlanID.name: apVlanID
apVlanID.description: VLAN tag for the packets trasmitted to/from Access Point. Value ranges: (-1) it is not tagged, zero(0) means reserved, 1-4094 tag value.

apIpAssignmentType.name: apIpAssignmentType
apIpAssignmentType.description: IP address assignment type, dhcp(1) = uses DHCP to obtain IP address, static(2) = static IP address is assigned to the access point.

apIfMAC.name: apIfMAC
apIfMAC.description: Acess Point's wired interface MAC address.

apIPAddress.name: apIPAddress
apIPAddress.description: Access Point's wired interface IP address.

apHwVersion.name: apHwVersion
apHwVersion.description: Text description of Access Point's hardware version.

apSwVersion.name: apSwVersion
apSwVersion.description: Text description of Access Point's major software version.

apHome.name: apHome
apHome.description: Local session is created when access point registers directly with the controller. Foreign session is mirrored session created via availability feature.

apRole.name: apRole
apRole.description: Indicates whether Access Point is a traffic fordwarder, sensor or guardian

apState.name: apState
apState.description: Active means that access point has registered with this controller at some point of time and still has active connection with this controller. This variable has meaning in the context of the controller that query is done. Inactive mean access point has lost the connection with this controller.

apStatus.name: apStatus
apStatus.description: Registration state for the access point at the time of query, approved(1) means the registration was completed, pending(2) means access point has registered but waiting manual approval from admin.

apPollTimeout.name: apPollTimeout
apPollTimeout.description: Duration after which the access point's connection to controller is considered has been lost if polling fails.

apPollInterval.name: apPollInterval
apPollInterval.description: Interval between each poll sent to the controller.

apTelnetAccess.name: apTelnetAccess
apTelnetAccess.description: Indicates whether telnet access is enabled/disabled. This value only applys to AP26xx, W788, W786 and AP4102x APs. 1 : Enabled. 2 : Disabled. 3 : Telnet is not supported.

apMaintainClientSession.name: apMaintainClientSession
apMaintainClientSession.description: If true, Access Point maintains client's session in the event of poll failure.

apRestartServiceContAbsent.name: apRestartServiceContAbsent
apRestartServiceContAbsent.description: If true, Access Point restarts the service in the absence of controller.

apLocation.name: apLocation
apLocation.description: Text identifying location of the access point.

apStaticMTUsize.name: apStaticMTUsize
apStaticMTUsize.description: Configured MTU size for the access point. Access point will use the lower value of MTU size between statically configured MTU size and dynamically learned MTU size.

apSiteID.name: apSiteID
apSiteID.description: The site ID, as defined in siteTable, that this AP is member of. The value of -1 indicates that AP is not member of any site.

apZone.name: apZone
apZone.description: The Zone to which the Access Point belongs.

apLLDP.name: apLLDP
apLLDP.description: Enable or disable broadcasting of LLDP information by the wireless AP.

apSSHAccess.name: apSSHAccess
apSSHAccess.description: Enable or Disable SSH access to the Wireless AP. This value only applys to AP36xx, AP37xx, W788C and W786C APs.

apLEDMode.name: apLEDMode
