apRegDiscoveryRetries.name: apRegDiscoveryRetries
apRegDiscoveryRetries.description: Number of retries for discovery requests from an access point to controller. After these number of retries, the access point will start over again after some arbitrary delays.

apRegDiscoveryInterval.name: apRegDiscoveryInterval
apRegDiscoveryInterval.description: Interval between two consecutive discovery requests from the same access point.

apRegTelnetPassword.name: apRegTelnetPassword
apRegTelnetPassword.description: Password used to access an AP via telnet. This field is write-only and read access returns empty string.

apRegSSHPassword.name: apRegSSHPassword
apRegSSHPassword.description: SSH password used to access an access point. This field is write-only and read access returns empty string.

apRegUseClusterEncryption.name: apRegUseClusterEncryption
apRegUseClusterEncryption.description: If this field set to true, then all APs in the cluster use cluster encryption.

apRegClusterSharedSecret.name: apRegClusterSharedSecret
apRegClusterSharedSecret.description: Password for cluster encryption. This field is write-only and read access returns empty string.

loadGroupTable.name: loadGroupTable
loadGroupTable.description: Table of configured load groups for access points. A set of access points can be grouped together and they are identified by unique name. An access point can only be assigned to one group.

loadGroupEntry.name: loadGroupEntry
loadGroupEntry.description: An entry containing definition of a load group. There exists two types of load group: client-balancing-group and radio-balancing-group.

loadGroupID.name: loadGroupID
loadGroupID.description: Internally generated ID for a group and cannot be changed externally.

loadGroupName.name: loadGroupName
loadGroupName.description: Unique name assigned to the group.

loadGroupType.name: loadGroupType
loadGroupType.description: Type of load balancing this group supports.

loadGroupBandPreference.name: loadGroupBandPreference
loadGroupBandPreference.description: Band preference is enabled for this group if this field is set to true and group type is set to radioBalancing(1).

loadGroupLoadControl.name: loadGroupLoadControl
loadGroupLoadControl.description: Load balancing is enabled for this group if this field is set to true and group type is set to radioBalancing(1).

loadGroupClientCountRadio1.name: loadGroupClientCountRadio1
loadGroupClientCountRadio1.description: Maximum number of client on this radio. This field is only applicable to a group with radioBalancing(1) type.

loadGroupClientCountRadio2.name: loadGroupClientCountRadio2
loadGroupClientCountRadio2.description: Maximum number of client on this radio. This field is only applicable to a group with radioBalancing(1) type.

loadGroupLoadControlEnableR1.name: loadGroupLoadControlEnableR1
loadGroupLoadControlEnableR1.description: If it is enabled then load control is applicable to radio #1 of all access points that are assigned to this load group. This field has meaning only for the load group that is of radioBalancing(1) type.

loadGroupLoadControlEnableR2.name: loadGroupLoadControlEnableR2
loadGroupLoadControlEnableR2.description: If it is enabled then load control is applicable to radio #2 of all access points that are assigned to this load group. This field has meaning only for the load group that is of radioBalancing(1) type.

loadGroupLoadControlStrictLimitR1.name: loadGroupLoadControlStrictLimitR1
loadGroupLoadControlStrictLimitR1.description: If it is enabled then strict limit for load control is applicable to radio #1 of all access points that are assigned to this load group. This field has meaning only for the load group that is of radioBalancing(1) type.

loadGroupLoadControlStrictLimitR2.name: loadGroupLoadControlStrictLimitR2
loadGroupLoadControlStrictLimitR2.description: If it is enabled then strict limit for load control is applicable to radio #2 of all access points that are assigned to this load group. This field has meaning only for the load group that is of radioBalancing(1) type.

loadGrpRadiosTable.name: loadGrpRadiosTable
loadGrpRadiosTable.description: Table of radio assignment to defined load groups.

loadGrpRadiosEntry.name: loadGrpRadiosEntry
loadGrpRadiosEntry.description: Any entry defining radio assignment of AP, identified by apIndex, to a load group identified by loadGroupID.

loadGrpRadiosRadio1.name: loadGrpRadiosRadio1
loadGrpRadiosRadio1.description: If this field is set to 'assigned(1)', then the radio of the AP identified by the apIndex is a member of the load balancing group identified by the loadBlanaceID. For radio blanacing group, either all or none of the radios of a specific AP (indentified by apIndex) are assigned to the load balancing group.

loadGrpRadiosRadio2.name: loadGrpRadiosRadio2
loadGrpRadiosRadio2.description: If this field is set to 'assigned(2)', then the radio of the AP identified by the apIndex is a member of the load balancing group identified by the loadBlanaceID. For radio blanacing group, either all or none of the radios of a specific AP (indentified by apIndex) are assigned to the load balancing group.

loadGrpWlanTable.name: loadGrpWlanTable
loadGrpWlanTable.description: Table of WLAN assignment to defined load groups.

loadGrpWlanEntry.name: loadGrpWlanEntry
loadGrpWlanEntry.description: An entry defining WLAN, identified by wlanID, assignment to a load group identified by loadGroupID.

loadGrpWlanAssigned.name: loadGrpWlanAssigned
loadGrpWlanAssigned.description: Assignement of WLAN, identified with wlanID, to the load balancing group identified bye loadGroupID.

schedule.name: schedule
schedule.description: AP maintenance schedule options. 0 : never perform the maintenance action. 1 : perform the maintenance action every day. 2 : perform the maintenance action every week. 3 : perform the maintenance action every month.

startHour.name: startHour
startHour.description: Maintenance action starts at this hour of the day.

startMinute.name: startMinute
startMinute.description: Maintenance action starts at this minute of the hour.

duration.name: duration
duration.description: Duration of the AP maintenance cycle (how often maintenance is done) in hours.

recurrenceDaily.name: recurrenceDaily
recurrenceDaily.description: This field has meaning only when the maintenance schedule option is set to daily(1). Below is the recurrence option. 0 : every day. 1 : every weekday. 2 : every weekend.

recurrenceWeekly.name: recurrenceWeekly
recurrenceWeekly.description: This field has meaning only when the maintenance schedule option is set to weekly(2). Below are the recurrence options. BIT 0 : Sunday. BIT 1 : Monday. BIT 2 : Tuesday. BIT 3 : Wednesday. BIT 4 : Thursday. BIT 5 : Friday. BIT 6 : Saturday.

recurrenceMonthly.name: recurrenceMonthly
recurrenceMonthly.description: This field has meaning only when the maintenance schedule option is set to monthly(3). Below are the recurrence options. BIT 0 : the first week of the month. BIT 1 : the second week of the month. BIT 2 : the third week of the month. BIT 3 : the fourth week of the month. BIT 4 : the fifth week of the month. BIT 5 : sunday of the week. BIT 6 : monday of the week. BIT 7 : tuesday of the week. BIT 8 : wednesday of the week. BIT 9 : thursday of the week. BIT 10 : friday of the week. BIT 11 : saturday of the week.

apPlatforms.name: apPlatforms
apPlatforms.description: Select which models of the AP platforms to perform the maintenance. BIT 0 : AP2600 platform. BIT 1 : AP2605 platform. BIT 2 : AP2650 platform. BIT 3 : AP4102 platform. BIT 4 : W786 platform. BIT 5 : AP3705 platform. BIT 6 : AP3710 platform. BIT 7 : AP3715 platform. BIT 8 : AP3765 platform. BIT 9 : AP3767 platform. BIT 10 : AP3801 platform. BIT 11 : AP3805 platform. BIT 12 : AP3825 platform. BIT 13 : AP3865 platform. BIT 14 : AP3935 platform. BIT 15 : AP3965 platform. BIT 16 : W78XC platform. BIT 17 : W78XCSFP platform.

mobileUnitCount.name: mobileUnitCount
mobileUnitCount.description: Number of clients associated with the controller.

muTable.name: muTable
muTable.description: Table of information for clients associated with the EWC.

muEntry.name: muEntry
muEntry.description: Information for a client associated with the EWC.

muState.name: muState
muState.description: True if the client is authenticated.

muAPSerialNo.name: muAPSerialNo
muAPSerialNo.description: Serial Number of the Access Point the client is associated with.

muVnsSSID.name: muVnsSSID
muVnsSSID.description: SSID of the VNS the client is associated with.

muTxPackets.name: muTxPackets
muTxPackets.description: Number of packets trasmitted to the client.

muRxPackets.name: muRxPackets
muRxPackets.description: Number of packets received from the client.

muTxOctets.name: muTxOctets
muTxOctets.description: Number of octets transmitted to the client.

muRxOctets.name: muRxOctets
muRxOctets.description: Number of octets received from the client.

muDuration.name: muDuration
muDuration.description: Time client has been associated with the EWC.

muAPName.name: muAPName
muAPName.description: Name of the Access Point the client is associated with.

muTopologyName.name: muTopologyName
muTopologyName.description: Topology name that the MU is associated with.

muPolicyName.name: muPolicyName
muPolicyName.description: The name of the policy that provides filter for this MU.

muDefaultCoS.name: muDefaultCoS
muDefaultCoS.description: The CoS that is applied to the current traffic if the defined rule for the current traffic has not specifically defined any CoS.

muConnectionProtocol.name: muConnectionProtocol
muConnectionProtocol.description: The MU is using this connection protocol for current connection. Symbols notation: n50 = an = n5.0Ghz, n24 = bgn = n2.4Ghz

muConnectionCapability.name: muConnectionCapability
muConnectionCapability.description: This field indicates what are the MU connection capability.

muWLANID.name: muWLANID
muWLANID.description: ID of the WLAN that the MU is associated with.

muDot11ConnectionCapability.name: muDot11ConnectionCapability
muDot11ConnectionCapability.description: This field indicates what are the MU connection capabilities. bit 0 : If this bit is set, the client is capable to tx/rx on A radio. bit 1 : If this bit is set, the client is capable to tx/rx on BG radio. bit 2 : If this bit is set, the client is capable of wpaV1 privacy. bit 3 : If this bit is set, the client is capable of wpaV2 privacy. bit 4 : If this bit is set, the client is capable to comunicate with 1 data stream. bit 5 : If this bit is set, the client is capable to comunicate with 2 data streams. bit 6 : If this bit is set, the client is capable to comunicate with 3 data streams. bit 7 : If this bit is set, the client is capable of Unscheduled automatic power-save delivery (U-APSD) benefits. The voice client can synchronize the transmission and reception of voice frames with the AP. bit 8 : If this bit is set, the client is capable of Unscheduled automatic power-save delivery (U-APSD) benefits. The video client can synchronize the transmission and reception of video frames with the AP. bit 9 : If this bit is set, the client is capable of Unscheduled automatic power-save delivery (U-APSD) benefits. The client can synchronize the transmission and reception in background queue. bit 10 : If this bit is set, the client is capable of Unscheduled automatic power-save delivery (U-APSD) benefits. The client can synchronize the transmission and reception in best effort queue. bit 11 : If this bit is set, the client is capable of Wi-Fi Multimedia(WMM) power save. bit 12 : If this bit is set, the client is capable of 802.11n Greenfield mode. bit 13 : If this bit is set, the client is on fast-transition mode.

muTSPECTable.name: muTSPECTable
muTSPECTable.description: Table of information for Admission Control Statistics by active client.

muTSPECEntry.name: muTSPECEntry
muTSPECEntry.description: Information for Admission Control Statistics by active client.

tspecAC.name: tspecAC
tspecAC.description: Access Category, such as Best Effort, Background, Voice, Video, and Reserved.

tspecDirection.name: tspecDirection
tspecDirection.description: Traffic direction, such as uplink direction, downlink direction.

muACLType.name: muACLType
muACLType.description: MUs can access EWC by sending association request and providing proper credentials. However, EWC allows creation of a master list of a blacklist or a whitelist group to control such access. There can exist only a blacklist or a whitelist (mutually exclusive) at any time. The list of MUs belonging to such a list is populated in muACLTable. The muACLTable content can be interpreted in conjunction with this field as follows: - blacklist(1): MUs listed in muACLTable cannot access EWC resources. - whitelist(2): Only MUs listed in muACLTable can access EWC resources.

muACLTable.name: muACLTable
muACLTable.description: Semantics of this list is directly related to muACLType. Access Control List(ACL) is list of MUs and their access rights. An MU can either belong to 'Blacklist', in that case its association request is denied, or it can belong to 'Whitelist', in that case it is allowed to associate to EWC provided having proper credentials.

muACLEntry.name: muACLEntry
muACLEntry.description: An entry about an MU and its ACL.

muACLRowStatus.name: muACLRowStatus
muACLRowStatus.description: An MU can either be added or removed to this list, therefore, allowed set values for this field are: createAndGo, destroy.

muAccessListTable.name: muAccessListTable
muAccessListTable.description: Semantics of this list is directly related to muACLType. Access List Control(ACL) list of MUs and their access rights. An MU can either belong to 'Blacklist', in that case its association request is denied, or it can belong to 'Whitelist', in that case it is allowed to associate to EWC provided having proper credentials.

muAccessListEntry.name: muAccessListEntry
muAccessListEntry.description: An entry about about an MU and its ACL.

muAccessListBitmaskLength.name: muAccessListBitmaskLength
muAccessListBitmaskLength.description: Length of bitmask associated to the MAC address in the entry.

muAccessListRowStatus.name: muAccessListRowStatus
muAccessListRowStatus.description: An MU can either be added or removed to this list, therefore, allowed set values for this field are: createAndGo, destroy.

assocCount.name: assocCount
assocCount.description: Total number of current client associations to the access point.

assocTable.name: assocTable
assocTable.description: Table of information about clients associated with the access point.

assocEntry.name: assocEntry
assocEntry.description: Information for a single client in the association table.

assocStartSysUpTime.name: assocStartSysUpTime
assocStartSysUpTime.description: The system uptime that client became associated with the access point.

assocTxPackets.name: assocTxPackets
assocTxPackets.description: Nubmer of tx packets to the client.

assocRxPackets.name: assocRxPackets
assocRxPackets.description: Number of received packets from the client.

assocTxOctets.name: assocTxOctets
assocTxOctets.description: Number of octets sent to the client.

assocRxOctets.name: assocRxOctets
assocRxOctets.description: Number of octets received from the client.

assocDuration.name: assocDuration
assocDuration.description: Length of time since last association.

assocVnsIfIndex.name: assocVnsIfIndex
assocVnsIfIndex.description: Index of VNS to which the MU is associated with.

logEventSeverityThreshold.name: logEventSeverityThreshold
logEventSeverityThreshold.description: Specifies the minimum level at which the SNMP agent will send notifications for log events. I.e., setting this value to 'major' will send notifcations for critical and major log events. Setting the threshold to minor will trap critical, major, and minor events.

logEventSeverity.name: logEventSeverity
logEventSeverity.description: Contains the severity of the most recently trapped hiPathWirelessLogAlarm notification.

logEventComponent.name: logEventComponent
logEventComponent.description: Contains the component which sent the most recently trapped hiPathWirelessLogAlarm notification.

logEventDescription.name: logEventDescription
logEventDescription.description: Contains the description of the most recently trapped hiPathWirelessLogAlarm.

siteMaxEntries.name: siteMaxEntries
siteMaxEntries.description: The maximum number of entries allowed in the siteTable. This value is platform dependent.

siteNumEntries.name: siteNumEntries
siteNumEntries.description: The current number of entries in the siteTable.

siteTableNextAvailableIndex.name: siteTableNextAvailableIndex
siteTableNextAvailableIndex.description: This object indicates the numerically lowest available index within this entity, which may be used for the value of siteID in the creation of a new entry in the siteTable. An index is considered available if the index value falls within the range of 1 to siteMaxEntries value and is not being used to index an existing entry in the siteTable contained within this entity. This value should only be considered a guideline for management creation of siteEntries, there is no requirement on management to create entries based upon this index value.

siteTable.name: siteTable
siteTable.description: A site is a logical entity that is constituted by collection of APs, CoS rules, policies, Radius server, WLAN, etc. A site is identified by a unique name.

siteID.name: siteID
siteID.description: An unique ID, identifying the site in the context of the controller. The site ID can be an integer value from 1 to the maximum number of APs supported by the EWC.

siteName.name: siteName
siteName.description: Textual description to identify the site in the context of the controller.

siteLocalRadiusAuthentication.name: siteLocalRadiusAuthentication
siteLocalRadiusAuthentication.description: If this value is set to true, then the RADIUS client is on APs, otherwise the RADIUS client is on controller.

siteDefaultDNSServer.name: siteDefaultDNSServer
siteDefaultDNSServer.description: If the APs associated to the site uses DHCP, and DHCP server does not assign DNS server, then this entry will be used for that purpose. Otherwise, if AP is configured with static IP address, then this entry will be used for that purpose.

siteEnableSecureTunnel.name: siteEnableSecureTunnel
siteEnableSecureTunnel.description: If set to true secure communication key sent to APs to be used to encrypt the traffic between APs within the site and the traffic between controller and APs. However, the encryption itself does not take place unless siteEncryptCommAPtoController and/or siteEncryptCommBetweenAPs set to true.

siteEncryptCommAPtoController.name: siteEncryptCommAPtoController
siteEncryptCommAPtoController.description: If set to true, communication between APs within the site and the controller are encrypted using defined encyption. For details about encryption type, please refer to user manual.

siteEncryptCommBetweenAPs.name: siteEncryptCommBetweenAPs
siteEncryptCommBetweenAPs.description: If set to true, communication between APs within the site are encrypted using defined encyption. For details about encryption type, please refer to user manual.

siteBandPreferenceEnable.name: siteBandPreferenceEnable
siteBandPreferenceEnable.description: Enabling/disabling band preference for the site and associated APs. By enabling band preference 11a-capable clients can be moved to 11a radio and relieve the congestion on the 11g radio. Band preference provides radio load balancing between 11g and 11a radios.

siteLoadControlEnableR1.name: siteLoadControlEnableR1
siteLoadControlEnableR1.description: Enabling/disabling load control for the site for this radio. Load control manages the number of clients on the Radio #1 by disallowing additional clients on the radio above the configured radio limit.

siteLoadControlEnableR2.name: siteLoadControlEnableR2
siteLoadControlEnableR2.description: Enabling/disabling load control for the site for this radio. Load control manages the number of clients on the Radio #2 by disallowing additional clients on the radio above the configured radio limit.

siteMaxClientR1.name: siteMaxClientR1
siteMaxClientR1.description: Maximum number of clients that are allowed to be associated to this radio (radio #1). If the Load Control is not enabled then the maximum for this radio uses default value.

siteMaxClientR2.name: siteMaxClientR2
siteMaxClientR2.description: Maximum number of clients that are allowed to be associated to this radio (radio #2). If the Load Control is not enabled then the maximum for this radio uses default value.

siteStrictLimitEnableR1.name: siteStrictLimitEnableR1
siteStrictLimitEnableR1.description: Enabling/disabling strict limit of load control for this radio that is assigned to the site. Eanbleing strict limit enforces configured client limit for the radio (radio #1) in any circumstances. Otherwise if this field is disabled then the restriction may not be enforced in all circumstances.

siteStrictLimitEnableR2.name: siteStrictLimitEnableR2
siteStrictLimitEnableR2.description: Enabling/disabling strict limit of load control for this radio that is assigned to the site. Eanbleing strict limit enforces configured client limit for the radio (radio #2) in any circumstances. Otherwise if this field is disabled then the restriction may not be enforced in all circumstances.

siteReplaceStnIDwithSiteName.name: siteReplaceStnIDwithSiteName
siteReplaceStnIDwithSiteName.description: If this value is set to true, then the called station ID will be replaced with the site name.

sitePolicyTable.name: sitePolicyTable
sitePolicyTable.description: Each site can have zero or more policies assigned to it. All policies associated to a site are pushed to the all APs belonging to the site. This table defines the assignment of various policies to various sites.

sitePolicyEntry.name: sitePolicyEntry
sitePolicyEntry.description: An entry defining assignment of a policy, identified by sitePolicyID, to a site, identified by siteID.

sitePolicyMember.name: sitePolicyMember
sitePolicyMember.description: Indicates whether the policy associated with this row is a member of the zone identified by zoneID.

siteCosTable.name: siteCosTable
siteCosTable.description: Each site can have zero or more CoS assigned to it. All CoS associated to a site are pushed to the all APs belonging to the site. This table defines the assignment of various CoS to various sites.

siteCosEntry.name: siteCosEntry
siteCosEntry.description: An entry defining assignment of a CoS, identified by siteCoSID, to a site, identified by siteID.

siteCoSID.name: siteCoSID
siteCoSID.description: The CoS index, as defined in ENTERASYS-POLICY-PROFILE-MIB::etsysCosIndex.

siteCoSMember.name: siteCoSMember
siteCoSMember.description: Indicates whether the CoS associated with this row is a member of the site identified by siteID.

siteAPTable.name: siteAPTable
siteAPTable.description: A site can have zero or more Access Points(AP) assigned to it. This table defines the assignment of various APs to various sites.

siteAPEntry.name: siteAPEntry
siteAPEntry.description: An entry defining assignment of an AP, identified by apIndex, to a site, identified by siteID.

siteAPMember.name: siteAPMember
siteAPMember.description: Indicates whether the AP associated with this row is a member of the site identified by siteID.

siteWlanTable.name: siteWlanTable
siteWlanTable.description: A site can have zero or more WLAN assigned to it. All WLANs that are associated with a site are pushed to the all APs belonging to the site. This table defines the assignment of various WLANs to various sites.

siteWlanEntry.name: siteWlanEntry
siteWlanEntry.description: An entry defining assignment of a WLAN identified by siteWlanID, to a site, identified by siteID.

mitigatorAnalysisEngine.name: mitigatorAnalysisEngine
mitigatorAnalysisEngine.description: Mitigator analysis engine can be enabled/disabled using this variable. All mitigator related objects, objects defined in widsWips subtree, can only be accessed using SNMPv3 provided this variable is set to enable(1) on behalf of users with privacy.

scanGroupMaxEntries.name: scanGroupMaxEntries
scanGroupMaxEntries.description: Maximum number of scan groups that can be created on the device.

scanGroupsCurrentEntries.name: scanGroupsCurrentEntries
scanGroupsCurrentEntries.description: Number of scan groups currently have been created on the device.

activeThreatsCounts.name: activeThreatsCounts
activeThreatsCounts.description: Number of currently active threats that have been detected.

friendlyAPCounts.name: friendlyAPCounts
friendlyAPCounts.description: Number of friendly access points that have been discovered at this point.

uncategorizedAPCounts.name: uncategorizedAPCounts
uncategorizedAPCounts.description: Number of uncategorized access points that have been discovered. This value refers to current number not the historical value.

widsWipsEngineTable.name: widsWipsEngineTable
widsWipsEngineTable.description: Table of Mitigators defined on set of controllers each identified by widsWipsEngineControllerIPAddress.

widsWipsEngineEntry.name: widsWipsEngineEntry
widsWipsEngineEntry.description: One entry in this table identifying a mitigator engine in a defined controller identified by IP address, widsWipsEngineControllerIPAddress.

widsWipsEngineRowStatus.name: widsWipsEngineRowStatus
widsWipsEngineRowStatus.description: RowStatus for creation/deletion of mitigator engine row.

widsWipsEngineControllerIPAddress.name: widsWipsEngineControllerIPAddress
widsWipsEngineControllerIPAddress.description: Ip address of the controller that the defined mitigator in this row will run on.

widsWipsEnginePollInterval.name: widsWipsEnginePollInterval
widsWipsEnginePollInterval.description: Poll interval in seconds between successive keep alive messages between this controller and the mitigator engine to monitor status of mitigator engine.

widsWipsEnginePollRetry.name: widsWipsEnginePollRetry
widsWipsEnginePollRetry.description: Number of consecutive retries of failed contact to a mitigator agent before declaring mitigator engine dead.

inServiceScanGroupTable.name: inServiceScanGroupTable
inServiceScanGroupTable.description: In service scan group enables the subsystem simultaneously scan for threats and performs wireless bridging based on 37xx-based APs. The threats are discovered and identified in the deployment environment and then classified for further actions.

inServiceScanGroupEntry.name: inServiceScanGroupEntry
inServiceScanGroupEntry.description: An entry in this table that defines attributes of a in-service scan group.

scanGroupProfileID.name: scanGroupProfileID
scanGroupProfileID.description: A internally unique identifier for a scan group. Each scan group is indexed by this value.

inSrvScanGrpName.name: inSrvScanGrpName
inSrvScanGrpName.description: Textual description identifying the scan group.

inSrvScanGrpSecurityThreats.name: inSrvScanGrpSecurityThreats
inSrvScanGrpSecurityThreats.description: Enable/disable security engine to scan for threats.

inSrvScanGrpMaxConcurrentAttacksPerAP.name: inSrvScanGrpMaxConcurrentAttacksPerAP
inSrvScanGrpMaxConcurrentAttacksPerAP.description: Max number of concurrent attacks per AP

inSrvScanGrpCounterMeasuresType.name: inSrvScanGrpCounterMeasuresType
inSrvScanGrpCounterMeasuresType.description: bit 0: Setting this bit prevents authorized stations from roaming to external honeypot APs. bit 1: Setting this bit prevents authorized stations from roaming to friendly APs. bit 2: Setting this bit prevents any station from using an internal honeypot AP. bit 3: Setting this bit prevents any station from using a spoofed AP. bit 4: Setting this bit drops frames in a controlled fashion during a flood attack. bit 5: Setting this bit removes network access from clients originating DoS attacks. bit 6: Setting this bit prevents any station from using an ad hoc mode device. bit 7: Setting this bit prevents any station from using a rogue AP.
